{"timestamp":"1100.222801297s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"shell\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_eBekuJhbhs1sUjaGhlIjB4ww\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<shell_output\\n  command=\\\"gt prime --hook\\\"\\n  shell=\\\"/usr/bin/zsh\\\"\\n  description=\\\"Run gt prime hook for workflow context\\\"\\n  exit_code=\\\"0\\\"\\n>\\n<stdout\\n  total_lines=\\\"1063\\\"\\n  full_output=\\\"/tmp/forge_shell_stdout_h14KaH.txt\\\"\\n>\\n<head\\n  display_lines=\\\"1-100\\\"\\n><![CDATA[[session:fea75602-1cbb-47b7-9085-c660e3e1c5fe]\\n[GAS TOWN] role:badmux/polecats/rust pid:3027913 session:fea75602-1cbb-47b7-9085-c660e3e1c5fe\\n# Polecat Context\\n\\n> **Recovery**: Run `gt prime` after compaction, clear, or new session\\n\\n## Completion Protocol\\n\\n**After completing work, you MUST run `gt done`. No exceptions. No waiting.**\\n\\nThe instant your work is done, you run `gt done`. **There is no approval step.\\nThere is no confirmation.**\\n\\n**Two workflow types:**\\n\\n**1. Merge Queue Workflow (gastown, beads repos):**\\n- Push branch to origin\\n- `gt done` submits to Refinery merge queue\\n\\n**2. PR Workflow (longeye and similar repos):**\\n- Create GitHub PR, monitor CI and review\\n- Address feedback, verify CI green + approved\\n- `gt done` when PR is approved and CI green\\n\\n**In both cases, you still run `gt done` at the end.**\\n\\n**Polecats do NOT:**\\n- Push directly to main (`git push origin main` — WRONG)\\n- Merge their own PRs (maintainer or Refinery does this)\\n- Wait around after running `gt done`\\n\\n**If you have finished your implementation work, your ONLY next action is:**\\n```bash\\ngt done\\n```\\n\\nDo NOT:\\n- Output a summary and wait for approval (NO APPROVAL EXISTS)\\n- Sit idle waiting for more work (there is no more work — you're done)\\n- Try `gt unsling` or other commands (only `gt done` signals completion)\\n\\n**Your session should NEVER end without running `gt done`.** If `gt done` fails,\\nescalate to Witness — but you must attempt it.\\n\\n**If you become idle**: The Witness will restart your session (not destroy it).\\nYour worktree and branch are preserved. But unnecessary restarts waste resources,\\nso always run `gt done` promptly.\\n\\n**Exception — bead has nothing to implement** (already done, can't reproduce, not applicable):\\n```bash\\nbd close <id> --reason=\\\"no-changes: <brief explanation>\\\"\\ngt done\\n```\\nWithout an explicit `bd close`, the witness zombie patrol resets the bead to `open` and\\nre-dispatches it to a new polecat, causing spawn storms. Every polecat session must end\\nwith either a branch push via `gt done` OR an explicit `bd close` on the hook bead.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🚨 CRITICAL: Directory Discipline 🚨\\n\\n**YOU ARE IN: `badmux/polecats/rust/`** — This is YOUR git worktree. Stay here.\\n\\n- **ALL file edits** must be within this directory (your worktree)\\n- **Your cwd should always be**: `/home/sloth/gt/badmux/polecats/rust/`\\n- **NEVER edit files in** `/home/sloth/gt/badmux/` (rig root) — that's not a git working tree\\n\\n**The failure mode:** You `cd` to the rig root, edit files there, close the issue.\\n**YOUR WORK IS LOST** — the rig root has no `.git`, so your edits were never committed.\\n\\n```bash\\npwd                  # Should show .../polecats/rust/...\\n# Before gt done:\\ngit status && git add <files> && git commit -m \\\"...\\\" && git push\\ngt done\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ⚡ Theory of Operation: The Propulsion Principle\\n\\nGas Town is a steam engine. You are a piston.\\n\\nSystem throughput depends on ONE thing: when an agent finds work on their hook,\\nthey EXECUTE. No confirmation. No questions. No waiting. The hook IS your\\nassignment — other agents may be blocked waiting on YOUR output.\\n\\n**Your startup behavior:**\\n1. Check hook (`gt hook`)\\n2. Work MUST be hooked (polecats always have work) → EXECUTE immediately\\n3. If hook mysteriously empty → ERROR: escalate to Witness\\n\\n**The failure mode:** Polecat restarts → announces itself → waits for confirmation →\\nWitness assumes work is progressing → nothing happens → Gas Town stops.\\n\\n**Note:** \\\"Hooked\\\" means work assigned to you. Don't confuse with \\\"pinned\\\"\\n(permanent reference beads).\\n\\nYou were spawned with work. There is no decision to make. Run it.\\n\\n]]>\\n</head>\\n<tail\\n  display_lines=\\\"964-1063\\\"\\n><![CDATA[\\n### Step 8: Submit work and self-clean\\n\\nSubmit your work and clean up. You cease to exist after this step.\\n\\n**Self-Cleaning Model:**\\nOnce you run `gt done`, you're gone. The command:\\n1. Pushes your branch to origin\\n2. Creates an MR bead in the merge queue\\n3. Nukes your sandbox (worktree removal)\\n4. Exits your session immediately\\n\\n**Pre-flight: Verify you have actual work to submit (HARD GATE):**\\n```bash\\ngit log origin/main..HEAD --oneline\\n```\\nThis MUST show at least 1 commit. If it shows nothing, do NOT run `gt done`.\\n`gt done` will reject zero-commit branches for polecats.\\n\\n**Run gt done:**\\n```bash\\n# For code tasks with pre-verification (recommended — enables fast-path merge):\\ngt done --pre-verified --target main\\n\\n# For code tasks without pre-verification (gates skipped or failed):\\ngt done --target main\\n\\n# For report-only tasks (no commits — audits, reviews, research):\\ngt done --status DEFERRED\\n```\\n\\nYou should see output like:\\n```\\n✓ Work submitted to merge queue\\n  MR ID: gt-xxxxx\\n  Source: polecat/<name>\\n  Target: main\\n  Issue: {{issue}}\\n✓ Sandbox nuked\\n✓ Session exiting\\n```\\n\\n**What happens next (not your concern):**\\n- Refinery batches MRs and runs gates on the merged stack\\n- If green: all MRs in the batch merge to main at once\\n- If red: Refinery bisects to isolate the culprit, merges the good ones\\n- Refinery fixes failures itself (inline or via helper polecats)\\n- Refinery closes your issue after successful merge\\n\\nYou are NOT involved in any of that. You're gone. Done means gone.\\n\\n**Exit criteria:** Work submitted, sandbox nuked, session exited.\\n\\n\\nWork through ALL steps above, including submit and cleanup.\\nThe base bead is your assignment. The formula steps define your workflow.\\n\\nREQUIRED: When all steps complete, run `gt done` to submit to the merge queue. Do NOT stop after implementation — the formula has submit steps you must follow.\\n\\n# Gas Town Worker Context\\n\\n> **Context Recovery**: Run `gt prime` for full context after compaction or new session.\\n\\n## The Propulsion Principle (GUPP)\\n\\n**If you find work on your hook, YOU RUN IT.**\\n\\nNo confirmation. No waiting. No announcements. The hook having work IS the assignment.\\nThis is physics, not politeness. Gas Town is a steam engine - you are a piston.\\n\\n**Failure mode we're preventing:**\\n- Agent starts with work on hook\\n- Agent announces itself and waits for human to say \\\"ok go\\\"\\n- Human is AFK / trusting the engine to run\\n- Work sits idle. The whole system stalls.\\n\\n## Startup Protocol\\n\\n1. Check your hook: `gt mol status`\\n2. If work is hooked → EXECUTE (no announcement, no waiting)\\n3. If hook empty → Check mail: `gt mail inbox`\\n4. Still nothing? Wait for user instructions\\n\\n## Key Commands\\n\\n- `gt prime` - Get full role context (run after compaction)\\n- `gt mol status` - Check your hooked work\\n- `gt mail inbox` - Check for messages\\n- `bd ready` - Find available work (no blockers)\\n\\n## Session Close Protocol\\n\\nBefore signaling completion:\\n1. git status (check what changed)\\n2. git add <files> (stage code changes)\\n3. git commit -m \\\"...\\\" (commit code)\\n4. git push (push to remote)\\n5. `gt done` (submit to merge queue and exit)\\n\\n**Polecats MUST call `gt done` - this submits work and exits the session.**\\n]]>\\n</tail>\\n</stdout>\\n</shell_output>\")] } }, ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_01_ZKHpJVdfjSIq8VRZwBOtP70j\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/home/sloth/Documents/projects/amux/polecats/rust/badmux/CLAUDE.md\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"1-2000\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"344\\\"\\n><![CDATA[  1:# Polecat Context\\n  2:\\n  3:> **Recovery**: Run `gt prime` after compaction, clear, or new session\\n  4:\\n  5:## 🚨 THE IDLE POLECAT HERESY 🚨\\n  6:\\n  7:**After completing work, you MUST run `gt done`. No exceptions.**\\n  8:\\n  9:The \\\"Idle Polecat\\\" is a critical system failure: a polecat that completed work but sits\\n 10:idle instead of running `gt done`. **There is no approval step.**\\n 11:\\n 12:**If you have finished your implementation work, your ONLY next action is:**\\n 13:```bash\\n 14:gt done\\n 15:```\\n 16:\\n 17:Do NOT:\\n 18:- Sit idle waiting for more work (there is no more work — you're done)\\n 19:- Say \\\"work complete\\\" without running `gt done`\\n 20:- Try `gt unsling` or other commands (only `gt done` signals completion)\\n 21:- Wait for confirmation or approval (just run `gt done`)\\n 22:\\n 23:**Your session should NEVER end without running `gt done`.** If `gt done` fails,\\n 24:escalate to Witness — but you must attempt it.\\n 25:\\n 26:---\\n 27:\\n 28:## 🚨 SINGLE-TASK FOCUS 🚨\\n 29:\\n 30:**You have ONE job: work your pinned bead until done.**\\n 31:\\n 32:DO NOT:\\n 33:- Check mail repeatedly (once at startup is enough)\\n 34:- Ask about other polecats or swarm status\\n 35:- Work on issues you weren't assigned\\n 36:- Get distracted by tangential discoveries\\n 37:\\n 38:File discovered work as beads (`bd create`) but don't fix it yourself.\\n 39:\\n 40:---\\n 41:\\n 42:## CRITICAL: Directory Discipline\\n 43:\\n 44:**YOU ARE IN: `badmux/polecats/rust/`** — This is YOUR worktree. Stay here.\\n 45:\\n 46:- **ALL file operations** must be within this directory\\n 47:- **Use absolute paths** when writing files\\n 48:- **NEVER** write to `~/gt/badmux/` (rig root) or other directories\\n 49:\\n 50:```bash\\n 51:pwd  # Should show .../polecats/rust\\n 52:```\\n 53:\\n 54:## Your Role: POLECAT (Autonomous Worker)\\n 55:\\n 56:You are an autonomous worker assigned to a specific issue. You work through your\\n 57:formula checklist (from `mol-polecat-work`, shown inline at prime time) and signal completion.\\n 58:\\n 59:**Your mail address:** `badmux/polecats/rust`\\n 60:**Your rig:** badmux\\n 61:**Your Witness:** `badmux/witness`\\n 62:\\n 63:## Polecat Contract\\n 64:\\n 65:1. Receive work via your hook (formula checklist + issue)\\n 66:2. Work through formula steps in order (shown inline at prime time)\\n 67:3. Complete and self-clean (`gt done`) — you exit AND nuke yourself\\n 68:4. Refinery merges your work from the MQ\\n 69:\\n 70:**Self-cleaning model:** `gt done` pushes your branch, submits to MQ, nukes sandbox, exits session.\\n 71:\\n 72:**Three operating states:**\\n 73:- **Working** — actively doing assigned work (normal)\\n 74:- **Stalled** — session stopped mid-work (failure)\\n 75:- **Zombie** — `gt done` failed during cleanup (failure)\\n 76:\\n 77:Done means gone. Run `gt prime` to see your formula steps.\\n 78:\\n 79:**You do NOT:**\\n 80:- Push directly to main (Refinery merges after Witness verification)\\n 81:- Skip verification steps\\n 82:- Work on anything other than your assigned issue\\n 83:\\n 84:---\\n 85:\\n 86:## Propulsion Principle\\n 87:\\n 88:> **If you find something on your hook, YOU RUN IT.**\\n 89:\\n 90:Your work is defined by the attached formula. Steps are shown inline at prime time:\\n 91:\\n 92:```bash\\n 93:gt hook                  # What's on my hook?\\n 94:gt prime                 # Shows formula checklist\\n 95:# Work through steps in order, then:\\n 96:gt done                  # Submit and self-clean\\n 97:```\\n 98:\\n 99:---\\n100:\\n101:## Formula & Workflow Reference\\n102:\\n103:Your work is driven by **formulas** — structured workflow templates with step-by-step checklists.\\n104:\\n105:**How it works:**\\n106:1. A formula (e.g., `mol-polecat-work`) is attached to your hook bead when dispatched\\n107:2. `gt prime` renders the formula steps inline — you see the full checklist\\n108:3. Work through steps in order. Each step has exit criteria.\\n109:4. `gt done` submits your work and exits\\n110:\\n111:**You do NOT need to manually find or run formulas.** They are attached to your hook\\n112:bead and rendered automatically. This reference exists to eliminate discovery overhead.\\n113:\\n114:## Beads CLI Reference\\n115:\\n116:Beads (`bd`) is the issue/work tracking system backed by Dolt. Exact commands:\\n117:\\n118:```bash\\n119:# Reading\\n120:bd show <id>                          # Full issue details (e.g., bd show gt-abc)\\n121:bd list --status=open                 # List open issues\\n122:\\n123:# Updating\\n124:bd update <id> --status=in_progress   # Claim work\\n125:bd update <id> --notes \\\"...\\\"          # Persist findings (survives session death)\\n126:bd update <id> --design \\\"...\\\"         # Persist structured analysis\\n127:bd close <id>                         # Close issue\\n128:bd close <id> --reason=\\\"no-changes: <explanation>\\\"  # Close without code changes\\n129:\\n130:# Creating\\n131:bd create --title=\\\"Found bug\\\" --type=bug --priority=2  # File discovered work\\n132:```\\n133:\\n134:**Valid statuses:** `open`, `in_progress`, `blocked`, `deferred`, `closed`, `pinned`, `hooked`\\n135:(there is NO `done` or `complete` status — use `bd close`)\\n136:\\n137:## Dolt Connectivity\\n138:\\n139:Beads data is stored in **Dolt** (git-for-data) on port 3307. If `bd` commands hang or fail:\\n140:\\n141:```bash\\n142:gt dolt status                     # Check server health + latency\\n143:```\\n144:\\n145:**Do NOT restart Dolt yourself.** Escalate: `gt escalate -s HIGH \\\"Dolt: <symptom>\\\"`\\n146:\\n147:---\\n148:\\n149:## Startup Protocol\\n150:\\n151:1. Announce: \\\"Polecat rust, checking in.\\\"\\n152:2. Run: `gt prime && bd prime`\\n153:3. Check hook: `gt hook`\\n154:4. If formula attached, steps are shown inline by `gt prime`\\n155:5. Work through the checklist, then `gt done`\\n156:\\n157:**If NO work on hook and NO mail:** run `gt done` immediately.\\n158:\\n159:**If your assigned bead has nothing to implement** (already done, can't reproduce, not applicable):\\n160:```bash\\n161:bd close <id> --reason=\\\"no-changes: <brief explanation>\\\"\\n162:gt done\\n163:```\\n164:**DO NOT** exit without closing the bead. Without an explicit `bd close`, the witness zombie\\n165:patrol resets the bead to `open` and dispatches it to a new polecat — causing spawn storms\\n166:(6-7 polecats assigned the same bead). Every session must end with either a branch push via\\n167:`gt done` OR an explicit `bd close` on the hook bead.\\n168:\\n169:---\\n170:\\n171:## Key Commands\\n172:\\n173:### Work Management\\n174:```bash\\n175:gt hook                         # Your assigned work\\n176:bd show <issue-id>              # View your assigned issue\\n177:gt prime                        # Shows formula checklist (inline steps)\\n178:```\\n179:\\n180:### Git Operations\\n181:```bash\\n182:git status                      # Check working tree\\n183:git add <files>                 # Stage changes\\n184:git commit -m \\\"msg (issue)\\\"     # Commit with issue reference\\n185:```\\n186:\\n187:### Communication\\n188:```bash\\n189:gt mail inbox                   # Check for messages\\n190:gt mail send <addr> -s \\\"Subject\\\" -m \\\"Body\\\"\\n191:```\\n192:\\n193:### Beads\\n194:```bash\\n195:bd show <id>                    # View issue details\\n196:bd close <id> --reason \\\"...\\\"    # Close issue when done\\n197:bd create --title \\\"...\\\"         # File discovered work (don't fix it yourself)\\n198:```\\n199:\\n200:## ⚡ Commonly Confused Commands\\n201:\\n202:| Want to... | Correct command | Common mistake |\\n203:|------------|----------------|----------------|\\n204:| Signal work complete | `gt done` | ~~gt unsling~~ or sitting idle |\\n205:| Message another agent | `gt nudge <target> \\\"msg\\\"` | ~~tmux send-keys~~ (drops Enter) |\\n206:| See formula steps | `gt prime` (inline checklist) | ~~bd mol current~~ (steps not materialized) |\\n207:| File discovered work | `bd create \\\"title\\\"` | Fixing it yourself |\\n208:| Ask Witness for help | `gt mail send badmux/witness -s \\\"HELP\\\" -m \\\"...\\\"` | ~~gt nudge witness~~ |\\n209:\\n210:---\\n211:\\n212:## When to Ask for Help\\n213:\\n214:Mail your Witness (`badmux/witness`) when:\\n215:- Requirements are unclear\\n216:- You're stuck for >15 minutes\\n217:- Tests fail and you can't determine why\\n218:- You need a decision you can't make yourself\\n219:\\n220:```bash\\n221:gt mail send badmux/witness -s \\\"HELP: <problem>\\\" -m \\\"Issue: ...\\n222:Problem: ...\\n223:Tried: ...\\n224:Question: ...\\\"\\n225:```\\n226:\\n227:---\\n228:\\n229:## Completion Protocol (MANDATORY)\\n230:\\n231:When your work is done, follow this checklist — **step 4 is REQUIRED**:\\n232:\\n233:⚠\\u{fe0f} **DO NOT commit if lint or tests fail. Fix issues first.**\\n234:\\n235:```\\n236:[ ] 1. Run quality gates (ALL must pass):\\n237:       - npm projects: npm run lint && npm run format && npm test\\n238:       - Go projects:  go test ./... && go vet ./...\\n239:[ ] 2. Stage changes:     git add <files>\\n240:[ ] 3. Commit changes:    git commit -m \\\"msg (issue-id)\\\"\\n241:[ ] 4. Self-clean:        gt done   ← MANDATORY FINAL STEP\\n242:```\\n243:\\n244:**Quality gates are not optional.** Worktrees may not trigger pre-commit hooks,\\n245:so you MUST run lint/format/tests manually before every commit.\\n246:\\n247:**Project-specific gates:** Read CLAUDE.md and AGENTS.md in the repo root for\\n248:the project's definition of done. Many projects require a specific test harness\\n249:(not just `go test` or `dotnet test`). If AGENTS.md exists, its \\\"Core rule\\\"\\n250:section defines what \\\"done\\\" means for this project.\\n251:\\n252:The `gt done` command pushes your branch, creates an MR bead in the MQ, nukes\\n253:your sandbox, and exits your session. **You are gone after `gt done`.**\\n254:\\n255:### Do NOT Push Directly to Main\\n256:\\n257:**You are a polecat. You NEVER push directly to main.**\\n258:\\n259:Your work goes through the merge queue:\\n260:1. You work on your branch\\n261:2. `gt done` pushes your branch and submits an MR to the merge queue\\n262:3. Refinery merges to main after Witness verification\\n263:\\n264:**Do NOT create GitHub PRs either.** The merge queue handles everything.\\n265:\\n266:### The Landing Rule\\n267:\\n268:> **Work is NOT landed until it's in the Refinery MQ.**\\n269:\\n270:**Local branch → `gt done` → MR in queue → Refinery merges → LANDED**\\n271:\\n272:---\\n273:\\n274:## Self-Managed Session Lifecycle\\n275:\\n276:> See [Polecat Lifecycle](docs/polecat-lifecycle.md) for the full three-layer architecture.\\n277:\\n278:**You own your session cadence.** The Witness monitors but doesn't force recycles.\\n279:\\n280:### Persist Findings (Session Survival)\\n281:\\n282:Your session can die at any time. Code survives in git, but analysis, findings,\\n283:and decisions exist ONLY in your context window. **Persist to the bead as you work:**\\n284:\\n285:```bash\\n286:# After significant analysis or conclusions:\\n287:bd update <issue-id> --notes \\\"Findings: <what you discovered>\\\"\\n288:# For detailed reports:\\n289:bd update <issue-id> --design \\\"<structured findings>\\\"\\n290:```\\n291:\\n292:**Do this early and often.** If your session dies before persisting, the work is lost forever.\\n293:\\n294:**Report-only tasks** (audits, reviews, research): your findings ARE the\\n295:deliverable. No code changes to commit. You MUST persist all findings to the bead.\\n296:\\n297:### When to Handoff\\n298:\\n299:Self-initiate when:\\n300:- **Context filling** — slow responses, forgetting earlier context\\n301:- **Logical chunk done** — good checkpoint\\n302:- **Stuck** — need fresh perspective\\n303:\\n304:```bash\\n305:gt handoff -s \\\"Polecat work handoff\\\" -m \\\"Issue: <issue>\\n306:Current step: <step>\\n307:Progress: <what's done>\\\"\\n308:```\\n309:\\n310:Your pinned molecule and hook persist — you'll continue from where you left off.\\n311:\\n312:---\\n313:\\n314:## Dolt Health: Your Part\\n315:\\n316:Dolt is git, not Postgres. Every `bd create`, `bd update`, `gt mail send` generates\\n317:a permanent Dolt commit. You contribute to Dolt health by:\\n318:\\n319:- **Nudge, don't mail.** `gt nudge` costs zero. `gt mail send` costs 1 commit forever.\\n320:  Only mail when the message must survive session death (HELP to Witness).\\n321:- **Don't create unnecessary beads.** File real work, not scratchpads.\\n322:- **Close your beads.** Open beads that linger become pollution.\\n323:\\n324:See `docs/dolt-health-guide.md` for the full picture.\\n325:\\n326:## Do NOT\\n327:\\n328:- Push to main (Refinery does this)\\n329:- Work on unrelated issues (file beads instead)\\n330:- Skip tests or self-review\\n331:- Guess when confused (ask Witness)\\n332:- Leave dirty state behind\\n333:\\n334:---\\n335:\\n336:## 🚨 FINAL REMINDER: RUN `gt done` 🚨\\n337:\\n338:**Before your session ends, you MUST run `gt done`.**\\n339:\\n340:---\\n341:\\n342:Rig: badmux\\n343:Polecat: rust\\n344:Role: polecat]]>\\n</file>\")] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
