{"timestamp":"1343.942047816s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Title generated for conversation","conversation_id":"b3f3a5ac-9694-46e3-a9f4-039fb9b9bbac","title":"Explore the codebase structure at /home/sloth/Documents/projects/amux/polecats/rust/badmux: 1) Find where App struct is defined - search for 'type App struct' in Go files, report the full struct definition with all fields and line numbers. 2) Find where UICompositor is defined - search for 'type UICompositor struct', report the full struct with all fields and methods. 3) Find files matching app_input_messages_dialogs.go and app_input_dialogs.go - report their full paths and key function signatures. 4) Find app_input.go - report its full path, all switch cases, and any areas needing updates for dialog/module handling. 5) Analyze the relationship between App and UICompositor - how does App reference UICompositor? Is it a field? How are they connected? 6) Find all handler methods related to dialogs (search for 'Dialog' in function names across internal/ directory)."},"filename":"crates/forge_app/src/hooks/tracing.rs","line_number":144}
{"timestamp":"1343.946646481s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"sage\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_yD71VTdln9q6o1UQVIVIIl2Q\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Explore the codebase structure at /home/sloth/Documents/projects/amux/polecats/rust/badmux: 1) Find where App struct is defined - search for 'type App struct' in Go files, report the full struct definition with all fields and line numbers. 2) Find where UICompositor is defined - search for 'type UICompositor struct', report the full struct with all fields and methods. 3) Find files matching app_input_messages_dialogs.go and app_input_dialogs.go - report their full paths and key function signatures. 4) Find app_input.go - report its full path, all switch cases, and any areas needing updates for dialog/module handling. 5) Analyze the relationship between App and UICompositor - how does App reference UICompositor? Is it a field? How are they connected? 6) Find all handler methods related to dialogs (search for 'Dialog' in function names across internal/ directory).\\\"\\n>\\n<output>Now I have all the information needed for a comprehensive report. Here is the full analysis:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Summary\\n\\nExplored the AMUX codebase structure focusing on the `App` struct, `UICompositor`, dialog-related handler methods, input routing, and the relationship between `App` and `UICompositor`. The codebase is a Go TUI application using the Charm Bubble Tea v2 framework.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. App Struct Definition\\n\\n**File:** `internal/app/app_core.go:40-126`\\n\\nThe `App` struct is the root Bubbletea model, encompassing:\\n\\n```go\\ntype App struct {\\n    // Configuration (lines 41-51)\\n    config           *config.Config\\n    workspaceService *workspaceService\\n    gitStatus        GitStatusService\\n    tmuxService      TmuxOps\\n    updateService    UpdateService\\n    modelRegistry    *discovery.Registry\\n    ticketServices   map[string]*tickets.TicketService\\n    doltStores       map[string]*dolt.ServerStore\\n    ticketRenderer   *tickets.Renderer\\n    discoveryReady   bool\\n\\n    // Limits (line 54)\\n    maxAttachedAgentTabs int\\n\\n    // State (lines 57-61)\\n    projects        []data.Project\\n    activeWorkspace *data.Workspace\\n    activeProject   *data.Project\\n    focusedPane     messages.PaneType\\n    showWelcome     bool\\n\\n    // Update state (lines 64-68)\\n    updateAvailable *update.CheckResult\\n    version         string\\n    commit          string\\n    buildDate       string\\n    upgradeRunning  bool\\n\\n    // UI Components (line 71)\\n    ui *UICompositor   // &lt;-- extracted to UICompositor\\n\\n    // Git status management (line 74)\\n    gitStatusController *GitStatusController\\n\\n    // Layout (line 77)\\n    keymap KeyMap\\n\\n    // Lifecycle (lines 79-82)\\n    err          error\\n    shutdownOnce sync.Once\\n    ctx          context.Context\\n    supervisor   *supervisor.Supervisor\\n\\n    // Prefix mode (lines 84-88)\\n    prefixActive    bool\\n    prefixToken     int\\n    prefixSequence  []string\\n    prefixLabel     string\\n    prefixHelpLabel string\\n\\n    // tmux activity tracking (lines 90-106, plus stanza lines 107-126)\\n    tmuxSyncToken             int\\n    tmuxActivityToken         int\\n    tmuxActivityScanInFlight  bool\\n    tmuxActivityRescanPending bool\\n    tmuxActivitySettled       bool\\n    tmuxActivitySettledScans  int\\n    tmuxActivityScannerOwner  bool\\n    tmuxActivityOwnershipSet  bool\\n    tmuxActivityOwnerEpoch    int64\\n    tmuxOptions               tmux.Options\\n    tmuxAvailable             bool\\n    tmuxCheckDone             bool\\n    projectsLoaded            bool\\n    tmuxInstallHint           string\\n    tmuxActiveWorkspaceIDs    map[string]bool\\n    sessionActivityStates     map[string]*activity.SessionState\\n    instanceID                string\\n    workspaceManager          *WorkspaceManager\\n    keyboardEnhancements      tea.KeyboardEnhancementsMsg\\n    lastInputAt               time.Time\\n    pendingInputLatency       bool\\n    externalMsgs              chan tea.Msg\\n    externalCritical          chan tea.Msg\\n    externalSender            func(tea.Msg)\\n    externalOnce              sync.Once\\n    ticketPoller              *ticketPoller\\n}\\n```\\n\\nDialog ID constants are declared at `app_core.go:23-32`:\\n- `DialogAddProject`, `DialogCreateWorkspace`, `DialogDeleteWorkspace`, `DialogRemoveProject`, `DialogSelectAssistant`, `DialogSelectTicket`, `DialogQuit`, `DialogCleanupTmux`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. UICompositor Struct Definition\\n\\n**File:** `internal/app/ui_compositor.go:21-76`\\n\\n```go\\ntype UICompositor struct {\\n    // Core UI component models (lines 22-30)\\n    layout          *layout.Manager\\n    dashboard       *dashboard.Model\\n    center          *center.Model\\n    sidebar         *sidebar.TabbedSidebar\\n    sidebarTerminal *sidebar.TerminalModel\\n    dialog          *common.Dialog         // lazy-created\\n    filePicker      *common.FilePicker     // lazy-created\\n    settingsDialog  *common.SettingsDialog // lazy-created\\n    toast           *common.ToastModel\\n\\n    // Dialog/picker context (lines 33-40)\\n    dialogProject           *data.Project\\n    dialogWorkspace         *data.Workspace\\n    pendingWorkspaceProject *data.Project\\n    pendingWorkspaceName    string\\n    pendingWorkspaceBase    string\\n    pendingTickets          []tickets.Ticket\\n    previewTicket           *tickets.Ticket\\n    previewProject          *data.Project\\n\\n    // Layout dimensions and visual state (lines 43-47)\\n    width, height int\\n    canvas        *lipgloss.Canvas\\n    styles        common.Styles\\n    ready         bool\\n    quitting      bool\\n\\n    // Chrome caches for layer-based rendering (lines 50-66)\\n    dashboardChrome      *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    centerChrome         *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    sidebarChrome        *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    dashboardContent     drawableCache\\n    dashboardBorders     borderCache\\n    sidebarTopTabBar     drawableCache\\n    // ... (sidebar and center content/border/status/help caches)\\n\\n    // Button focus state (lines 69-70)\\n    centerBtnFocused bool\\n    centerBtnIndex   int\\n\\n    // Settings theme dialog state (lines 73-75)\\n    settingsDialogSession       int\\n    settingsThemePersistedTheme common.ThemeID\\n    settingsThemeDirty          bool\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Methods on UICompositor:** Only one method exists directly — `canvasFor(width, height int) *lipgloss.Canvas` at `ui_compositor.go:99-111`, which lazily creates/resizes a canvas for rendering.\\n\\n**Constructor:** `newUICompositor()` at `ui_compositor.go:81-95` initializes non-lazy fields (layout, dashboard, center, sidebar, sidebarTerminal, toast, chrome caches, styles). Lazy fields (`dialog`, `filePicker`, `settingsDialog`) start `nil`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Dialog-Related Files\\n\\n| File | Full Path |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| `app_input_messages_dialogs.go` | `/home/sloth/Documents/projects/amux/polecats/rust/badmux/internal/app/app_input_messages_dialogs.go` (340 lines) |\\n| `app_input_dialogs.go` | `/home/sloth/Documents/projects/amux/polecats/rust/badmux/internal/app/app_input_dialogs.go` (346 lines) |\\n\\n**Key function signatures in `app_input_messages_dialogs.go`:**\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 20 | `func (a *App) handleShowAddProjectDialog()` |\\n| 35 | `func (a *App) handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog(msg messages.ShowCreateWorkspaceDialog)` |\\n| 54 | `func (a *App) handleShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog(msg messages.ShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog)` |\\n| 68 | `func (a *App) handleShowRemoveProjectDialog(msg messages.ShowRemoveProjectDialog)` |\\n| 85 | `func (a *App) handleShowSelectAssistantDialog()` |\\n| 98 | `func (a *App) handleShowSelectTicketDialog() tea.Cmd` |\\n| 117 | `func (a *App) handleTicketsForPickerLoaded(msg ticketsForPickerLoaded)` |\\n| 140 | `func (a *App) handleShowCleanupTmuxDialog()` |\\n| 155 | `func (a *App) handleShowSettingsDialog()` |\\n| 183 | `func (a *App) applyTheme(theme common.ThemeID)` |\\n| 200 | `func (a *App) handleThemePreview(msg common.ThemePreview) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 211 | `func (a *App) persistSettingsThemeIfDirty() tea.Cmd` |\\n| 225 | `func (a *App) handleSettingsResult(_ common.SettingsResult) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 236 | `func (a *App) handleTicketSelected(msg messages.TicketSelectedMsg) []tea.Cmd` |\\n| 275 | `func (a *App) handleTicketPreview(msg messages.TicketPreviewMsg)` |\\n| 288 | `func sortTicketsHierarchically(ts []tickets.Ticket) []tickets.Ticket` |\\n\\n**Key function signatures in `app_input_dialogs.go`:**\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 18 | `func (a *App) handleDialogResultMsg(msg tea.Msg) (bool, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 34 | `func (a *App) handleErrorOverlayDismiss(msg tea.Msg) bool` |\\n| 48 | `func handleOverlayInput[T ...](overlay T, msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd, consumePaste bool) (T, bool)` |\\n| 68 | `func isNilOverlay[T any](overlay T) bool` |\\n| 81 | `func (a *App) handleDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 87 | `func (a *App) handleFilePickerInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 93 | `func (a *App) handleSettingsDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 100 | `func (a *App) handleDialogResult(result common.DialogResult) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 244 | `func (a *App) showQuitDialog()` |\\n| 259 | `func (a *App) handleUpdateCheckComplete(msg messages.UpdateCheckComplete) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 284 | `func (a *App) handleTriggerUpgrade() tea.Cmd` |\\n| 318 | `func (a *App) handleUpgradeComplete(msg messages.UpgradeComplete) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 335 | `func (a *App) handleOpenFileInEditor(msg sidebar.OpenFileInEditor) tea.Cmd` |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. app_input.go — Full Path and Analysis\\n\\n**Path:** `/home/sloth/Documents/projects/amux/polecats/rust/badmux/internal/app/app_input.go` (390 lines)\\n\\nThe `update()` function at `app_input.go:31-383` is the core message router. Its switch statement has these cases:\\n\\n| Line | Case | Handler/Hint |\\n|------|------|-------------|\\n| 39-42 | `tea.KeyPressMsg, tea.KeyReleaseMsg, tea.MouseClickMsg, ...` | Perf input marking |\\n| 45-47 | `handleDialogResultMsg(msg)` | **Dialog layer check (checked FIRST before overlay input)** |\\n| 48-50 | `handleErrorOverlayDismiss(msg)` | Error dismiss |\\n| 53-57 | `common.ToastDismissed` | Toast updates |\\n| 59-67 | `handleDialogInput`, `handleFilePickerInput`, `handleSettingsDialogInput` | **Overlay input gates (KeyPress + Mouse captured BEFORE pane routing)** |\\n| 69-71 | `tea.KeyboardEnhancementsMsg` | Keyboard capabilities |\\n| 73-74 | `tea.WindowSizeMsg` | Resize |\\n| 76-79 | `tea.MouseClickMsg, tea.MouseWheelMsg, ...` | Mouse to `handleMouseMsg` |\\n| 81-84 | `tea.PasteMsg` | Paste routing |\\n| 86-87 | `prefixTimeoutMsg` | Prefix timer |\\n| 89-92 | `tea.KeyPressMsg` | Keyboard to `handleKeyPress` |\\n| 94-95 | `messages.ProjectsLoaded` | Projects loaded |\\n| 97-98 | `messages.WorkspaceActivated` | Workspace activation |\\n| 100-101 | `messages.ShowWelcome` | Go home |\\n| 103-106 | `messages.ShowCommandsPalette` | Command palette |\\n| 108-112 | `messages.ToggleKeymapHints` | Toggle hints |\\n| 114-115 | `messages.ShowQuitDialog` | **Quit dialog** |\\n| 117-118 | `messages.RefreshDashboard` | Refresh |\\n| 120-121 | `messages.RescanWorkspaces` | Rescan |\\n| 123-128 | `messages.WorkspaceCreatedWithWarning`, `WorkspaceCreated` | Workspace creation |\\n| 130-137 | `WorkspaceSetupComplete`, `WorkspaceCreateFailed` | Workspace lifecycle |\\n| 139-140 | `messages.GitStatusResult` | Git status |\\n| 142-143 | `messages.ShowAddProjectDialog` | **Add project dialog** |\\n| 145-146 | `messages.ShowCreateWorkspaceDialog` | **Create workspace dialog** |\\n| 148-149 | `messages.ShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog` | **Delete workspace dialog** |\\n| 151-152 | `messages.ShowRemoveProjectDialog` | **Remove project dialog** |\\n| 154-155 | `messages.ShowSelectAssistantDialog` | **Assistant picker dialog** |\\n| 157-160 | `messages.ShowSelectTicketDialog` | **Ticket picker dialog** |\\n| 162-163 | `ticketsForPickerLoaded` | **Ticket data loaded for picker** |\\n| 165-166 | `messages.TicketSelectedMsg` | **Ticket selected from dialog** |\\n| 168-169 | `messages.TicketPreviewMsg` | Ticket hover preview |\\n| 171-172 | `messages.ShowSettingsDialog` | **Settings dialog** |\\n| 174-175 | `messages.ShowCleanupTmuxDialog` | **Tmux cleanup dialog** |\\n| 177-180 | `common.ThemePreview` | Theme preview |\\n| 182-185 | `common.SettingsResult` | Settings close |\\n| 187-188 et al. | Many more workspace/agent/tab/tmux/update/etc. cases | Infrastructure messages |\\n| 373-380 | `default` | Forward to center pane |\\n\\n**Areas needing updates for dialog/module handling:**\\n\\n1. **Dispatch order**: `handleDialogResultMsg` is checked at line 45-47, *before* the three `handleDialogInput`/`handleFilePickerInput`/`handleSettingsDialogInput` checks at lines 59-67. This means a `DialogResult` message always gets consumed even if it also matches a child component's update. The fallback at line 28-31 sends unmatched dialog IDs to `a.ui.center`.\\n\\n2. **Overlay input gating**: Lines 59-67 act as a gate — if any dialog/filePicker/settingsDialog is visible, `KeyPressMsg` and `MouseClickMsg` are consumed by that overlay and never reach pane routing below (line 69+). This is correct but means new overlay types must be added to this gate explicitly.\\n\\n3. **Hard-coded dialog ID list**: In `app_input_dialogs.go:25`, the switch case lists all known dialog IDs as literal strings. Adding a new dialog type requires updating this list or it will fall through to `a.ui.center.Update()`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. Relationship Between App and UICompositor\\n\\n`App` references `UICompositor` as a **single direct field**:\\n\\n```go\\n// internal/app/app_core.go:71\\nui *UICompositor\\n```\\n\\nThe relationship is **composition/delegation** (not embedding). `App` is the owner and `UICompositor` is a subordinate struct holding all visual state.\\n\\n**Connection patterns:**\\n\\n- **Creation**: `App` presumably instantiates `UICompositor` via `newUICompositor(cfg, styles)` at initialization (this call is not in `app_core.go` but likely in an init/constructor elsewhere).\\n\\n- **All dialog access goes through `a.ui.*`**: Every dialog handler method accesses dialog state via `a.ui.dialog`, `a.ui.filePicker`, `a.ui.settingsDialog`, `a.ui.dialogProject`, `a.ui.pendingTickets`, etc. Examples:\\n  - `app_input_messages_dialogs.go:26`: `a.ui.filePicker = common.NewFilePicker(...)`\\n  - `app_input_dialogs.go:83-84`: `a.ui.dialog, consumed = handleOverlayInput(a.ui.dialog, msg, cmds, true)`\\n  - `app_input_dialogs.go:103-105`: `a.ui.dialog = nil; a.ui.dialogProject = nil; a.ui.dialogWorkspace = nil`\\n\\n- **Rendering**: `composeOverlays()` at `app_view_overlays.go:16-86` checks `a.ui.dialog`, `a.ui.filePicker`, `a.ui.settingsDialog` for visibility and renders them as overlay layers on the canvas.\\n\\n- **Cursor management**: `overlayCursor()` at `app_view_overlays.go:179-206` checks dialog/filePicker cursor position and offsets it to the centered overlay position.\\n\\n- **Visibility check**: `overlayVisible()` at `app_view_overlays.go:208-214` checks all three overlay types plus prefix mode and error state.\\n\\n- **Pane components** (`dashboard`, `center`, `sidebar`, `sidebarTerminal`, `toast`) are also accessed through `a.ui.*` — the UICompositor owns all visual model state, while `App` retains business logic, services, lifecycle, and message routing.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. All Handler Methods Related to Dialogs\\n\\nFound across these files in `internal/`:\\n\\n### `internal/app/app_input_dialogs.go`\\n| Line | Method | Purpose |\\n|------|--------|---------|\\n| 18 | `handleDialogResultMsg(msg tea.Msg) (bool, tea.Cmd)` | Routes dialog results by ID; falls back to center pane for unknown IDs |\\n| 34 | `handleErrorOverlayDismiss(msg tea.Msg) bool` | Dismisses error overlay on mouse click |\\n| 81 | `handleDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` | Routes input to `a.ui.dialog` overlay |\\n| 87 | `handleFilePickerInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` | Routes input to `a.ui.filePicker` overlay |\\n| 93 | `handleSettingsDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` | Routes input to `a.ui.settingsDialog` overlay |\\n| 100 | `handleDialogResult(result common.DialogResult) tea.Cmd` | Core dialog completion handler — dispatches based on dialog ID |\\n| 244 | `showQuitDialog()` | Shows the quit confirmation dialog |\\n\\n### `internal/app/app_input_messages_dialogs.go`\\n| Line | Method | Purpose |\\n|------|--------|---------|\\n| 20 | `handleShowAddProjectDialog()` | Opens file picker for adding a project |\\n| 35 | `handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog(msg)` | Opens input dialog for workspace name |\\n| 54 | `handleShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog(msg)` | Opens confirm dialog for workspace deletion |\\n| 68 | `handleShowRemoveProjectDialog(msg)` | Opens confirm dialog for project removal |\\n| 85 | `handleShowSelectAssistantDialog()` | Opens agent picker dialog |\\n| 98 | `handleShowSelectTicketDialog() tea.Cmd` | Opens ticket picker (or falls back to assistant picker) |\\n| 117 | `handleTicketsForPickerLoaded(msg)` | Populates ticket picker with loaded tickets |\\n| 140 | `handleShowCleanupTmuxDialog()` | Opens confirm dialog for tmux session cleanup |\\n| 155 | `handleShowSettingsDialog()` | Opens the settings/theme dialog |\\n| 183 | `applyTheme(theme)` | Applies a theme to all UI components |\\n| 200 | `handleThemePreview(msg) tea.Cmd` | Live theme preview handler |\\n| 211 | `persistSettingsThemeIfDirty() tea.Cmd` | Saves theme to config if changed |\\n| 225 | `handleSettingsResult(_ common.SettingsResult) tea.Cmd` | Closes settings dialog and persists theme |\\n| 236 | `handleTicketSelected(msg) []tea.Cmd` | Handles ticket selection from dashboard picker |\\n| 275 | `handleTicketPreview(msg)` | Updates preview state on ticket hover |\\n\\n### `internal/app/app_input_dialogs.go` (update/infrastructure dialog handlers)\\n| Line | Method | Purpose |\\n|------|--------|---------|\\n| 259 | `handleUpdateCheckComplete(msg) tea.Cmd` | Processes update check results |\\n| 284 | `handleTriggerUpgrade() tea.Cmd` | Triggers self-upgrade flow |\\n| 318 | `handleUpgradeComplete(msg) tea.Cmd` | Handles upgrade completion |\\n| 335 | `handleOpenFileInEditor(msg) tea.Cmd` | Opens file in vim from sidebar file tree |\\n\\n### Additional dialog-related files in `internal/ui/common/`\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|------|---------|\\n| `ui/common/dialog.go` | Base `Dialog` component implementation |\\n| `ui/common/dialog_render.go` | Dialog rendering |\\n| `ui/common/dialog_update.go` | Dialog update logic |\\n| `ui/common/dialog_test.go` | Dialog tests |\\n| `ui/common/agent_picker.go` | Agent picker (implements `Dialog` interface) |\\n| `ui/common/ticket_picker.go` | Ticket picker (implements `Dialog` interface) |\\n| `ui/common/filepicker.go` | File picker component |\\n| `ui/common/filepicker_navigation.go` | File picker keyboard nav |\\n| `ui/common/settings.go` | Settings dialog component |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Follow-up Suggestions\\n\\n1. **Dialog ID list maintenance**: The hard-coded list at `app_input_dialogs.go:25` should be kept in sync with the constants at `app_core.go:23-32`. Consider using a map/set or deriving from constants to prevent drift.\\n\\n2. **Overlay input gate extensibility**: Lines 59-67 in `app_input.go` gate overlay input. Adding a new overlay type (beyond dialog/filePicker/settingsDialog) requires updating this gate, the `overlayVisible()` method, the `overlayCursor()` method, and the `composeOverlays()` render method.\\n\\n3. **UICompositor method density**: Currently `UICompositor` has only one method (`canvasFor`). All dialog manipulation is done by `App` methods directly accessing `a.ui.dialog` etc. As decomposition continues, consider moving dialog lifecycle methods onto `UICompositor`.\\n\\n4. **Testing**: Dialog tests exist in `app_input_messages_dialogs_test.go` (theme/settings) and `app_input_ticket_dialog_test.go` (ticket picker flow). No tests were found covering the add project, remove project, create/delete workspace, or assistant picker dialog flows directly.</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(b3f3a5ac-9694-46e3-a9f4-039fb9b9bbac) }, AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Search for the App struct definition in /home/sloth/Documents/projects/amux/polecats/rust/badmux - find 'type App struct' in all .go files and return the complete struct definition with line numbers, all fields, and the file path.\\\"\\n>\\n<output>## Results\\n\\nThe `App` struct is defined in **`internal/app/app_core.go:40-126`**. Here is the complete definition:\\n\\n```\\ninternal/app/app_core.go:40-126\\n```\\n\\n```go\\ntype App struct {\\n\\t// Configuration\\n\\tconfig           *config.Config\\n\\tworkspaceService *workspaceService\\n\\tgitStatus        GitStatusService\\n\\ttmuxService      TmuxOps\\n\\tupdateService    UpdateService\\n\\tmodelRegistry    *discovery.Registry\\n\\tticketServices   map[string]*tickets.TicketService\\n\\tdoltStores       map[string]*dolt.ServerStore\\n\\tticketRenderer   *tickets.Renderer\\n\\tdiscoveryReady   bool\\n\\n\\t// Limits\\n\\tmaxAttachedAgentTabs int\\n\\n\\t// State\\n\\tprojects        []data.Project\\n\\tactiveWorkspace *data.Workspace\\n\\tactiveProject   *data.Project\\n\\tfocusedPane     messages.PaneType\\n\\tshowWelcome     bool\\n\\n\\t// Update state\\n\\tupdateAvailable *update.CheckResult // nil if no update or dismissed\\n\\tversion         string\\n\\tcommit          string\\n\\tbuildDate       string\\n\\tupgradeRunning  bool\\n\\n\\t// UI Components (extracted to UICompositor)\\n\\tui *UICompositor\\n\\n\\t// Git status management\\n\\tgitStatusController *GitStatusController\\n\\n\\t// Layout\\n\\tkeymap KeyMap\\n\\t// Lifecycle\\n\\terr          error\\n\\tshutdownOnce sync.Once\\n\\tctx          context.Context\\n\\tsupervisor   *supervisor.Supervisor\\n\\t// Prefix mode (leader key)\\n\\tprefixActive    bool\\n\\tprefixToken     int\\n\\tprefixSequence  []string\\n\\tprefixLabel     string\\n\\tprefixHelpLabel string\\n\\n\\ttmuxSyncToken             int\\n\\ttmuxActivityToken         int\\n\\ttmuxActivityScanInFlight  bool\\n\\ttmuxActivityRescanPending bool\\n\\ttmuxActivitySettled       bool\\n\\ttmuxActivitySettledScans  int\\n\\ttmuxActivityScannerOwner  bool\\n\\ttmuxActivityOwnershipSet  bool\\n\\ttmuxActivityOwnerEpoch    int64\\n\\ttmuxOptions               tmux.Options\\n\\ttmuxAvailable             bool\\n\\ttmuxCheckDone             bool\\n\\tprojectsLoaded            bool\\n\\ttmuxInstallHint           string\\n\\ttmuxActiveWorkspaceIDs    map[string]bool\\n\\tsessionActivityStates     map[string]*activity.SessionState // Per-session hysteresis state\\n\\tinstanceID                string                            // Immutable after init; safe for read-only access from Cmd goroutines.\\n\\n\\t// Workspace lifecycle manager\\n\\tworkspaceManager *WorkspaceManager\\n\\n\\t// Terminal capabilities\\n\\tkeyboardEnhancements tea.KeyboardEnhancementsMsg\\n\\n\\t// Perf tracking\\n\\tlastInputAt         time.Time\\n\\tpendingInputLatency bool\\n\\n\\t// External message pump (for PTY readers)\\n\\texternalMsgs     chan tea.Msg\\n\\texternalCritical chan tea.Msg\\n\\texternalSender   func(tea.Msg)\\n\\texternalOnce     sync.Once\\n\\n\\t// Ticket auto-refresh: supervisor worker that polls LatestUpdate() off-thread.\\n\\tticketPoller *ticketPoller\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Summary of 11 field groups (81 lines, 126 lines total including closing brace):\\n\\n| # | Group | Fields |\\n|---|-------|--------|\\n| 1 | **Configuration** (lines 42-51) | `config`, `workspaceService`, `gitStatus`, `tmuxService`, `updateService`, `modelRegistry`, `ticketServices`, `doltStores`, `ticketRenderer`, `discoveryReady` |\\n| 2 | **Limits** (line 54) | `maxAttachedAgentTabs` |\\n| 3 | **State** (lines 57-61) | `projects`, `activeWorkspace`, `activeProject`, `focusedPane`, `showWelcome` |\\n| 4 | **Update state** (lines 64-68) | `updateAvailable`, `version`, `commit`, `buildDate`, `upgradeRunning` |\\n| 5 | **UI Components** (line 71) | `ui` (`*UICompositor`) |\\n| 6 | **Git status management** (line 74) | `gitStatusController` |\\n| 7 | **Layout / Lifecycle / Prefix mode** (lines 77-88) | `keymap`, `err`, `shutdownOnce`, `ctx`, `supervisor`, `prefixActive`, `prefixToken`, `prefixSequence`, `prefixLabel`, `prefixHelpLabel` |\\n| 8 | **tmux state** (lines 90-106) | 18 fields covering sync, activity scanning, options, availability, workspace tracking, session activity states, and `instanceID` |\\n| 9 | **Workspace lifecycle** (line 109) | `workspaceManager` |\\n| 10 | **Terminal / Perf** (lines 112-116) | `keyboardEnhancements`, `lastInputAt`, `pendingInputLatency` |\\n| 11 | **External message pump &amp; Ticket poller** (lines 119-125) | `externalMsgs`, `externalCritical`, `externalSender`, `externalOnce`, `ticketPoller` |\\n\\nThe struct is instantiated via the `NewApp` constructor at `internal/app/app_core.go:135`. A lazy-initialized workspace manager accessor `wm()` is provided at line 130, allowing test code to construct `App` without explicitly setting `workspaceManager`.</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(7dc40b0e-38d0-4202-a144-b95a10b69959) }, AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Find the UICompositor struct definition - search for 'type UICompositor' and return the complete struct definition with all fields, embedded types, methods list, and file path with line numbers.\\\"\\n>\\n<output>Here are the complete findings:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Summary\\n\\nThe `UICompositor` struct is a core UI composition type defined in `internal/app/ui_compositor.go`. It was extracted from a larger `App` \\\"god object\\\" as part of a gradual decomposition effort, holding the main UI component models that together form the main screen layout.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Struct Definition\\n\\n**File:** `internal/app/ui_compositor.go:21-76`\\n\\n```go\\ntype UICompositor struct {\\n    layout          *layout.Manager\\n    dashboard       *dashboard.Model\\n    center          *center.Model\\n    sidebar         *sidebar.TabbedSidebar\\n    sidebarTerminal *sidebar.TerminalModel\\n    dialog          *common.Dialog         // lazy-created\\n    filePicker      *common.FilePicker     // lazy-created\\n    settingsDialog  *common.SettingsDialog // lazy-created\\n    toast           *common.ToastModel\\n\\n    // Dialog/picker context (moved from App).\\n    dialogProject           *data.Project\\n    dialogWorkspace         *data.Workspace\\n    pendingWorkspaceProject *data.Project\\n    pendingWorkspaceName    string\\n    pendingWorkspaceBase    string\\n    pendingTickets          []tickets.Ticket\\n    previewTicket           *tickets.Ticket\\n    previewProject          *data.Project\\n\\n    // Layout dimensions and visual state (moved from App).\\n    width, height int\\n    canvas        *lipgloss.Canvas // nil initially, lazy-created\\n    styles        common.Styles\\n    ready         bool\\n    quitting      bool\\n\\n    // Chrome caches for layer-based rendering (moved from App).\\n    dashboardChrome      *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    centerChrome         *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    sidebarChrome        *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    dashboardContent     drawableCache\\n    dashboardBorders     borderCache\\n    sidebarTopTabBar     drawableCache\\n    sidebarTopContent    drawableCache\\n    sidebarBottomContent drawableCache\\n    sidebarBottomTabBar  drawableCache\\n    sidebarBottomStatus  drawableCache\\n    sidebarBottomHelp    drawableCache\\n    sidebarTopBorders    borderCache\\n    sidebarBottomBorders borderCache\\n    centerTabBar         drawableCache\\n    centerStatus         drawableCache\\n    centerHelp           drawableCache\\n    centerBorders        borderCache\\n\\n    // Button focus state for welcome/workspace info screens (moved from App).\\n    centerBtnFocused bool\\n    centerBtnIndex   int\\n\\n    // Settings theme dialog state (moved from App).\\n    settingsDialogSession       int\\n    settingsThemePersistedTheme common.ThemeID\\n    settingsThemeDirty          bool\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Embedded / Nested Types\\n\\n| Type | Defined In | Purpose |\\n|------|-----------|---------|\\n| `drawableCache` | `internal/app/app_cache.go:8-12` | Caches a string-based drawable by content + position |\\n| `borderCache` | `internal/app/app_cache.go:30-36` | Caches a set of border `StringDrawable`s by position, size, and theme |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Methods\\n\\n**Direct receiver (`*UICompositor`):**\\n\\n| Method | File | Line | Signature |\\n|--------|------|------|-----------|\\n| `canvasFor` | `internal/app/ui_compositor.go` | 99 | `func (u *UICompositor) canvasFor(width, height int) *lipgloss.Canvas` |\\n\\nThis is the **only** method with `UICompositor` as its receiver. The struct is primarily a data holder; its methods likely live on the `App` struct or the `compositor` package that consume it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Field Groupings\\n\\n1. **Core UI components** (lines 22-30): The five main sub-models — `layout`, `dashboard`, `center`, `sidebar`, `sidebarTerminal`, plus three lazy-created overlay models (`dialog`, `filePicker`, `settingsDialog`) and `toast`.\\n\\n2. **Dialog/picker context** (lines 32-40): State data for dialogs and pickers, including project/workspace references, pending workspace info, ticket lists, and preview references.\\n\\n3. **Layout &amp; visual state** (lines 42-47): Terminal dimensions (`width`, `height`), the Lip Gloss `canvas`, shared `styles`, and lifecycle booleans (`ready`, `quitting`).\\n\\n4. **Rendering caches** (lines 49-66): Three `compositor.ChromeCache` pointers for dashboard/center/sidebar, plus 14 inline cache fields (`drawableCache` / `borderCache`) for specific UI regions (e.g., `sidebarTopTabBar`, `centerBorders`).\\n\\n5. **Button/misc state** (lines 68-75): Focus tracking for center-area buttons and settings-theme dialog session state.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Constructor\\n\\n**File:** `internal/app/ui_compositor.go:81-95`\\n\\n`newUICompositor(cfg *config.Config, styles common.Styles) *UICompositor` — initializes all non-lazy fields (layout, dashboard, center, sidebar, sidebarTerminal, toast, styles, and the three chrome caches). Lazy fields (`dialog`, `filePicker`, `settingsDialog`, `canvas`) start as `nil`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Follow-up Suggestions\\n\\n- The struct has few dedicated methods; most logic consuming it likely lives on the `App` struct or in `internal/ui/compositor`. Investigating `App` struct methods that operate on `UICompositor` fields would reveal the full interaction surface.\\n- The `ChromeCache`, `StringDrawable`, and `compositor` package types referenced are worth exploring for understanding the layer-based rendering model.</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(69ba7c79-8d76-4dbe-96d9-a9c5638480c4) }, AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Find all files matching patterns *dialog* in the internal/ directory tree - report full paths and key content summaries (function signatures, struct types).\\\"\\n>\\n<output>Here is the complete report of all 7 `*dialog*` files in the `internal/` directory tree.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File Inventory\\n\\n| # | Full Path | Lines |\\n|---|-----------|-------|\\n| 1 | `internal/ui/common/dialog.go` | 223 |\\n| 2 | `internal/ui/common/dialog_render.go` | 278 |\\n| 3 | `internal/ui/common/dialog_update.go` | 230 |\\n| 4 | `internal/ui/common/dialog_test.go` | 463 |\\n| 5 | `internal/app/app_input_dialogs.go` | 346 |\\n| 6 | `internal/app/app_input_messages_dialogs.go` | 340 |\\n| 7 | `internal/app/app_input_ticket_dialog_test.go` | 172 |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. `internal/ui/common/dialog.go` (223 lines)\\n\\n**Package:** `common`\\n\\n### Types\\n\\n| Type | Kind | Lines | Description |\\n|------|------|-------|-------------|\\n| `DialogType` | `int` enum | `10-18` | `DialogNone`, `DialogInput`, `DialogConfirm`, `DialogSelect` |\\n| `DialogResult` | struct | `21-26` | Fields: `ID string`, `Confirmed bool`, `Value string`, `Index int` — sent when dialog completes |\\n| `InputTransformFunc` | func type | `29` | `func(string) string` — transforms input before adding to field |\\n| `InputValidateFunc` | func type | `32` | `func(string) string` — validates input, empty = valid |\\n| `Dialog` | struct | `35-68` | Core modal dialog component with fields for config, state, input handling, fuzzy filter, ticket items, layout, option hit regions |\\n| `dialogOptionHit` | struct | `70-74` | Associates a `cursorIndex`, `optionIndex`, and `HitRegion` for mouse-click targeting |\\n\\n### Constructor Functions\\n\\n| Function | Lines | Signature |\\n|----------|-------|-----------|\\n| `NewInputDialog` | `77-91` | `func NewInputDialog(id, title, placeholder string) *Dialog` |\\n| `NewConfirmDialog` | `94-103` | `func NewConfirmDialog(id, title, message string) *Dialog` |\\n| `NewSelectDialog` | `106-115` | `func NewSelectDialog(id, title, message string, options []string) *Dialog` |\\n\\n### Methods on `*Dialog`\\n\\n| Method | Lines | Signature |\\n|--------|-------|-----------|\\n| `SetInputTransform` | `134-137` | `func (d *Dialog) SetInputTransform(fn InputTransformFunc) *Dialog` |\\n| `SetInputValidate` | `140-143` | `func (d *Dialog) SetInputValidate(fn InputValidateFunc) *Dialog` |\\n| `Show` | `167-180` | `func (d *Dialog) Show()` — makes dialog visible, resets state |\\n| `Hide` | `199-201` | `func (d *Dialog) Hide()` |\\n| `Visible` | `204-206` | `func (d *Dialog) Visible() bool` |\\n| `SetShowKeymapHints` | `209-211` | `func (d *Dialog) SetShowKeymapHints(show bool)` |\\n| `SetSize` | `214-223` | `func (d *Dialog) SetSize(width, height int)` |\\n\\n### Internal Helpers\\n\\n| Function | Lines | Signature |\\n|----------|-------|-----------|\\n| `fuzzyMatch` | `118-131` | `func fuzzyMatch(pattern, target string) bool` — case-insensitive subsequence match |\\n| `transformInputMsg` | `146-164` | `func (d *Dialog) transformInputMsg(msg tea.Msg) tea.Msg` — applies transform to key/paste msgs |\\n| `applyFilter` | `184-196` | `func (d *Dialog) applyFilter()` — updates `filteredIndices` based on `filterInput` |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. `internal/ui/common/dialog_render.go` (278 lines)\\n\\n**Package:** `common`\\n\\n### Functions\\n\\n| Function | Lines | Signature |\\n|----------|-------|-----------|\\n| `viewDimensions` | `11-20` | `func viewDimensions(view string) (width, height int)` — measures rendered string dimensions |\\n| `(*Dialog).View` | `23-31` | `func (d *Dialog) View() string` — main render entry; returns empty if not visible |\\n| `(*Dialog).Cursor` | `34-80` | `func (d *Dialog) Cursor() *tea.Cursor` — returns cursor position relative to dialog view (handles input &amp; filter) |\\n| `(*Dialog).dialogContentWidth` | `82-88` | `func (d *Dialog) dialogContentWidth() int` — clamps to [50, 80] |\\n| `(*Dialog).dialogStyle` | `90-96` | `func (d *Dialog) dialogStyle() lipgloss.Style` — rounded border, primary color, padding |\\n| `(*Dialog).dialogFrame` | `98-103` | `func (d *Dialog) dialogFrame() (frameX, frameY, offsetX, offsetY int)` |\\n| `(*Dialog).renderedLineCount` | `108-114` | `func (d *Dialog) renderedLineCount(rawLines []string) int` — accounts for word-wrap |\\n| `(*Dialog).renderLines` | `116-174` | `func (d *Dialog) renderLines() []string` — builds all content lines, dispatches by dialog type |\\n| `(*Dialog).renderOptionsLines` | `176-184` | `func (d *Dialog) renderOptionsLines(baseLine int) []string` — dispatches to agent/ticket/horizontal renderers |\\n| `(*Dialog).renderHorizontalOptionsLine` | `186-221` | `func (d *Dialog) renderHorizontalOptionsLine(baseLine int) string` — flat option buttons with hit regions |\\n| `(*Dialog).renderInputButtonsLine` | `223-246` | `func (d *Dialog) renderInputButtonsLine(baseLine int) string` — OK/Cancel buttons for input dialog |\\n| `(*Dialog).addOptionHit` | `248-262` | `func (d *Dialog) addOptionHit(cursorIdx, optionIdx, line, x, width int)` — registers a clickable hit region |\\n| `(*Dialog).helpText` | `264-277` | `func (d *Dialog) helpText() string` — returns keymap hint string per dialog type |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. `internal/ui/common/dialog_update.go` (230 lines)\\n\\n**Package:** `common`\\n\\n### Functions\\n\\n| Function | Lines | Signature |\\n|----------|-------|-----------|\\n| `(*Dialog).Update` | `13-157` | `func (d *Dialog) Update(msg tea.Msg) (*Dialog, tea.Cmd)` — main update loop; handles `esc`, `enter`, navigation keys (`tab`/`down`/`up`/`h`/`l`/`left`/`right`), delegates to textinput/filter updates, and mouse clicks |\\n| `(*Dialog).handleClick` | `159-230` | `func (d *Dialog) handleClick(msg tea.MouseClickMsg) tea.Cmd` — converts mouse coordinates to local dialog coordinates, checks hit regions, returns `DialogResult` cmds |\\n\\n### Key Update Behavior\\n- **Esc**: hides dialog, returns `DialogResult{Confirmed: false}` (`dialog_update.go:28-32`)\\n- **Enter on Input**: blocks if validation error exists; otherwise returns value (`dialog_update.go:34-52`)\\n- **Enter on Confirm**: returns `Confirmed: cursor == 0` (Yes if cursor 0) (`dialog_update.go:53-60`)\\n- **Enter on Select**: respects filter; returns original option index (`dialog_update.go:61-87`)\\n- **Tab/Down/Up**: cycles cursor through options, filtered if applicable (`dialog_update.go:89-112`)\\n- **h/l/left/right**: jumps cursor on Confirm dialogs (`dialog_update.go:114-123`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. `internal/ui/common/dialog_test.go` (463 lines)\\n\\n**Package:** `common`\\n\\n### Test Functions\\n\\n| Function | Lines | What It Tests |\\n|----------|-------|---------------|\\n| `TestDialogCursorHiddenWhenNotVisible` | `11-16` | Cursor returns nil when hidden |\\n| `TestDialogCursorPositionInput` | `18-46` | Cursor offset calculation for input dialog (title + border/padding) |\\n| `TestDialogCursorPositionFilter` | `48-79` | Cursor offset for agent picker with filter input |\\n| `TestDialogConfirmClickYes` | `81-150` | Full mouse-click flow: render → coordinate transform → hit-region lookup → DialogResult.Verified=true |\\n| `TestDialogConfirmClickNo` | `152-203` | Click \\\"No\\\" → Confirmed=false |\\n| `TestDialogInputClickCancel` | `205-257` | Click Cancel on input dialog → Confirmed=false |\\n| `TestDialogConfirmClickYesWrappingMessage` | `265-337` | Click Yes when message text wraps across lines; verifies `renderedLineCount` correctly handles wrapping |\\n| `TestDialogConfirmClickNoWrappingMessage` | `339-391` | Click No with wrapping message |\\n| `TestDialogSelectClickWrappingMessage` | `393-463` | Click first option in select dialog with wrapping message; verifies Index and Value |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. `internal/app/app_input_dialogs.go` (346 lines)\\n\\n**Package:** `app`\\n\\n### Functions on `*App`\\n\\n| Function | Lines | Signature |\\n|----------|-------|-----------|\\n| `handleDialogResultMsg` | `18-32` | `func (a *App) handleDialogResultMsg(msg tea.Msg) (bool, tea.Cmd)` — routes `DialogResult` by ID; falls through to center pane for unknown IDs |\\n| `handleErrorOverlayDismiss` | `34-44` | `func (a *App) handleErrorOverlayDismiss(msg tea.Msg) bool` — dismisses error overlay on click |\\n| `handleOverlayInput` | `48-66` | Generic function `func handleOverlayInput[T interface{Visible() bool; Update(tea.Msg) (T, tea.Cmd)}](overlay T, msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd, consumePaste bool) (T, bool)` — dispatches input to any modal overlay |\\n| `isNilOverlay` | `68-79` | `func isNilOverlay[T any](overlay T) bool` — nil-check via reflection |\\n| `handleDialogInput` | `81-85` | `func (a *App) handleDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| `handleFilePickerInput` | `87-91` | `func (a *App) handleFilePickerInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| `handleSettingsDialogInput` | `93-97` | `func (a *App) handleSettingsDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| `handleDialogResult` | `100-242` | `func (a *App) handleDialogResult(result common.DialogResult) tea.Cmd` — **central dialog-result dispatcher** handling all known dialog IDs |\\n| `showQuitDialog` | `244-256` | `func (a *App) showQuitDialog()` — creates a \\\"Quit AMUX\\\" confirm dialog |\\n| `handleUpdateCheckComplete` | `259-281` | `func (a *App) handleUpdateCheckComplete(msg messages.UpdateCheckComplete) tea.Cmd` |\\n| `handleTriggerUpgrade` | `284-315` | `func (a *App) handleTriggerUpgrade() tea.Cmd` |\\n| `handleUpgradeComplete` | `318-331` | `func (a *App) handleUpgradeComplete(msg messages.UpgradeComplete) tea.Cmd` |\\n| `handleOpenFileInEditor` | `335-346` | `func (a *App) handleOpenFileInEditor(msg sidebar.OpenFileInEditor) tea.Cmd` |\\n\\n### Dialog ID Constants (referenced from `handleDialogResultMsg` at `app_input_dialogs.go:25`)\\n\\n`DialogAddProject`, `DialogCreateWorkspace`, `DialogDeleteWorkspace`, `DialogRemoveProject`, `DialogSelectAssistant`, `DialogSelectTicket`, `DialogQuit`, `DialogCleanupTmux`, plus string literals `\\\"agent-picker\\\"` and `\\\"ticket-picker\\\"`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. `internal/app/app_input_messages_dialogs.go` (340 lines)\\n\\n**Package:** `app`\\n\\n### Functions on `*App`\\n\\n| Function | Lines | Signature |\\n|----------|-------|-----------|\\n| `handleShowAddProjectDialog` | `20-32` | `func (a *App) handleShowAddProjectDialog()` — opens file picker |\\n| `handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog` | `35-51` | `func (a *App) handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog(msg messages.ShowCreateWorkspaceDialog)` — input dialog with validation |\\n| `handleShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog` | `54-