rnal message carrying loaded tickets for the picker dialog |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7. `internal/app/app_input_ticket_dialog_test.go` (172 lines)\\n\\n**Package:** `app`\\n\\n### Test Functions\\n\\n| Function | Lines | What It Tests |\\n|----------|-------|---------------|\\n| `TestHandleShowSelectTicketDialog_NoTicketService_FallbackToAssistant` | `13-34` | When no ticket service exists, falls back to `ShowSelectAssistantDialog` |\\n| `TestHandleShowSelectTicketDialog_NoActiveWorkspace` | `36-52` | Returns nil cmd when no active workspace |\\n| `TestHandleTicketsForPickerLoaded` | `54-83` | Dialog created and visible with \\\"Select Ticket\\\" title; 2 pending tickets |\\n| `TestTicketPickerResult_StartsDraftFlow` | `85-123` | Confirmed ticket-picker result emits `TicketSelectedMsg` with correct ticket &amp; project; clears pending |\\n| `TestTicketPickerResult_NoTicketOption` | `125-152` | Index &gt;= len(pendingTickets) → falls back to assistant picker |\\n| `TestTicketPickerResult_Cancel` | `154-172` | `Confirmed: false` → pending tickets cleared to nil |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture Summary\\n\\nThe dialog subsystem follows a **model-view-update** pattern (Bubble Tea v2):\\n\\n```\\ninternal/ui/common/          (reusable dialog component)\\n  ├── dialog.go               Model: Dialog struct, constructors, config\\n  ├── dialog_render.go        View: lipgloss rendering, cursor/hit-region tracking\\n  ├── dialog_update.go        Update: key/mouse event handling, state transitions\\n  └── dialog_test.go          Unit tests: cursor positions, click hit regions, wrapping\\n\\ninternal/app/                 (app-level dialog orchestration)\\n  ├── app_input_dialogs.go          Dialog routing, result dispatching, lifecycle (quit/upgrade)\\n  ├── app_input_messages_dialogs.go Dialog creation in response to messages, ticket/agent pickers\\n  └── app_input_ticket_dialog_test.go   Integration tests for ticket dialog flow\\n```\\n\\n**Key design points:**\\n- The `Dialog` struct (`dialog.go:35-68`) supports three modes (`DialogInput`, `DialogConfirm`, `DialogSelect`) plus optional fuzzy filtering and ticket/agent specializations\\n- Mouse-click hit regions are computed during render via `dialogOptionHit` records (`dialog.go:70-74`, `dialog_render.go:248-262`) and resolved in `handleClick` (`dialog_update.go:159-230`)\\n- The generic `handleOverlayInput` function (`app_input_dialogs.go:48-66`) provides a reusable pattern for dispatching input to any modal overlay (dialog, file picker, settings dialog)\\n- `handleDialogResult` (`app_input_dialogs.go:100-242`) is the central dispatch that converts dialog completions into business-logic messages\\n- Ticket dialogs follow a two-phase flow: load tickets asynchronously (`ticketsForPickerLoaded` internal message), then create the picker dialog (`handleTicketsForPickerLoaded` at `app_input_messages_dialogs.go:117-137`)</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(27777ccc-9f1e-41b4-9120-383d55087208) }, AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Find app_input.go file - read it completely and report all switch case statements, function signatures, and identify areas related to dialog or module handling.\\\"\\n>\\n<output>Here is the complete analysis of `internal/app/app_input.go`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File Overview\\n\\n**Path:** `internal/app/app_input.go`\\n**Lines:** 390\\n**Package:** `app`\\n**Imports:** 7 packages (line 3-15):\\n- `fmt`, `runtime/debug`\\n- `tea \\\"charm.land/bubbletea/v2\\\"`\\n- `github.com/andyrewlee/amux/internal/logging`\\n- `github.com/andyrewlee/amux/internal/messages`\\n- `github.com/andyrewlee/amux/internal/perf`\\n- `github.com/andyrewlee/amux/internal/ui/center`\\n- `github.com/andyrewlee/amux/internal/ui/common`\\n- `github.com/andyrewlee/amux/internal/ui/dashboard`\\n- `github.com/andyrewlee/amux/internal/ui/sidebar`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Function Signatures\\n\\n| # | Signature | Line | Description |\\n|---|-----------|------|-------------|\\n| 1 | 