owRemoveProjectDialog(msg)` |\\n| `messages.ShowSelectAssistantDialog` | 154-155 | `a.handleShowSelectAssistantDialog()` |\\n| `messages.ShowSelectTicketDialog` | 157-160 | `a.handleShowSelectTicketDialog()` |\\n| `messages.ShowSettingsDialog` | 171-172 | `a.handleShowSettingsDialog()` |\\n| `messages.ShowCleanupTmuxDialog` | 174-175 | `a.handleShowCleanupTmuxDialog()` |\\n| `common.ThemePreview` | 177-180 | `a.handleThemePreview` |\\n| `common.SettingsResult` | 182-185 | `a.handleSettingsResult` |\\n\\n#### Ticket Handling\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `ticketsForPickerLoaded` | 162-163 | `a.handleTicketsForPickerLoaded` |\\n| `messages.TicketSelectedMsg` | 165-166 | `a.handleTicketSelected` |\\n| `messages.TicketPreviewMsg` | 168-169 | `a.handleTicketPreview` |\\n| `ticketStoreResult` | 346-347 | `a.handleTicketStoreResult` |\\n| `messages.TicketsLoadedMsg` | 349-356 | Forwarded to `a.ui.dashboard.Update` |\\n\\n#### Tab Handling\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler(s) |\\n|---------|-------|------------|\\n| `messages.OpenDiff` | 204-207 | `a.handleOpenDiff` |\\n| `messages.CloseTab` | 209-211 | `a.ui.center.CloseActiveTab()` |\\n| `messages.LaunchAgent` | 213-216 | `a.handleLaunchAgent` |\\n| `messages.TabCreated` | 218-225 | `a.handleTabCreated` + `enforceAttachedAgentTabLimit` + `persistActiveWorkspaceTabs` |\\n| `messages.TabClosed` | 227-231 | log + `persistActiveWorkspaceTabs` |\\n| `messages.TabDetached` | 233-237 | log + `a.handleTabDetached` |\\n| `messages.TabReattached` | 239-241 | `enforceAttachedAgentTabLimit` + `persistWorkspaceTabs` |\\n| `messages.TabStateChanged` | 243-244 | `a.persistWorkspaceTabs` |\\n| `messages.TabSelectionChanged` | 246-247 | `a.persistWorkspaceTabs` |\\n\\n#### PTY Handling (Center &amp; Sidebar)\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `center.PTYOutput, center.PTYTick, center.PTYFlush, center.PTYStopped` | 252-260 | `a.handlePTYMessages` + spinner/dashboard sync |\\n| `center.TabInputFailed` | 262-263 | `a.handleTabInputFailed` |\\n| `messages.SidebarPTYOutput, messages.SidebarPTYTick, messages.SidebarPTYFlush, messages.SidebarPTYStopped, messages.SidebarPTYRestart, sidebar.SidebarTerminalCreated, sidebar.SidebarTerminalCreateFailed, sidebar.SidebarTerminalReattachResult, sidebar.SidebarTerminalReattachFailed, sidebar.SidebarSelectionScrollTick` | 277-280 | `a.handleSidebarPTYMessages` |\\n| `sidebar.OpenFileInEditor` | 282-285 | `a.handleOpenFileInEditor` |\\n\\n#### Toast\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `messages.Toast` | 266-275 | Inner switch on `msg.Level` (Success/Error/Warning/default) dispatching to `a.ui.toast.ShowSuccess/Error/Warning/Info` |\\n\\nThis contains a nested switch:\\n\\n```go\\ncase messages.Toast:                          // line 265\\n    switch msg.Level {                        // line 266\\n    case messages.ToastSuccess:               // line 267\\n    case messages.ToastError:                 // line 269\\n    case messages.ToastWarning:               // line 271\\n    default:                                  // line 273 (info)\\n    }\\n```\\n\\n#### Tmux Activity\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `tmuxActivityTick` | 298-299 | `a.handleTmuxActivityTick` |\\n| `tmuxActivityResult` | 300-301 | `a.handleTmuxActivityResult` |\\n| `tmuxAvailableResult` | 302-303 | `a.handleTmuxAvailableResult` |\\n| `messages.TmuxSyncTick` | 304-305 | `a.handleTmuxSyncTick` |\\n| `tmuxTabsSyncResult` | 307-308 | `a.handleTmuxTabsSyncResult` |\\n| `tmuxTabsDiscoverResult` | 309-310 | `a.handleTmuxTabsDiscoverResult` |\\n| `tmuxSidebarDiscoverResult` | 311-312 | `a.handleTmuxSidebarDiscoverResult` |\\n\\n#### Tick / GC / System Messages\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `dashboard.SpinnerTickMsg` | 287-288 | `a.handleSpinnerTick` |\\n| `messages.GitStatusTick` | 290-291 | `a.gitStatusController.HandleGitStatusTick` |\\n| `messages.OrphanGCTick` | 293-294 | `a.handleOrphanGCTick` |\\n| `messages.PTYWatchdogTick` | 296-297 | `a.handlePTYWatchdogTick` |\\n| `orphanGCResult` | 313-314 | `a.handleOrphanGCResult` |\\n| `staleDetachedAgentGCResult` | 315-316 | `a.handleStaleDetachedAgentGCResult` |\\n| `sessionCountResult` | 317-318 | `a.handleSessionCountResult` |\\n| `persistDebounceMsg` | 249-250 | `a.handlePersistDebounce` |\\n\\n#### File Watcher / State Watcher\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `messages.FileWatcherEvent` | 320-321 | `a.gitStatusController.HandleFileWatcherEvent` |\\n| `messages.StateWatcherEvent` | 323-324 | `a.gitStatusController.HandleStateWatcherEvent` |\\n\\n#### Updates / Upgrades\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `messages.UpdateCheckComplete` | 338-341 | `a.handleUpdateCheckComplete` |\\n| `messages.TriggerUpgrade` | 358-361 | `a.handleTriggerUpgrade` |\\n| `messages.UpgradeComplete` | 363-366 | `a.handleUpgradeComplete` |\\n\\n#### Error\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `messages.Error` | 368-371 | `a.handleErrorMessage` |\\n\\n#### Default (catch-all)\\n\\n| Case | Lines | Handler |\\n|------|-------|---------|\\n| `default` | 373-379 | Forwards to `a.ui.center.Update(msg)` for unknown message types (e.g., commit viewer internal messages) |\\n\\n#### Other\\n\\n| Case(s) | Lines | Handler |\\n|---------|-------|---------|\\n| `messages.ToggleKeymapHints` | 108-112 | Toggles hint setting + saves config |\\n| `messages.GitStatusResult` | 139-140 | `a.gitStatusController.HandleGitStatusResult` |\\n| `messages.DiscoveryLoadedMsg` | 343-344 | `a.handleDiscoveryLoaded` |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Dialog &amp; Module Handling: Deep Dive\\n\\n### Dialog Flow Architecture\\n\\nThe dialog system uses a two-tier dispatch pattern:\\n\\n1. **Pre-main-switch guards (lines 45-67):** Four guard functions intercept messages before the main switch. If any return `true`, the update returns immediately:\\n\\n   - `a.handleDialogResultMsg(msg)` — line 45: Handles dialog result messages (e.g., confirm/cancel actions from modal dialogs).\\n   - `a.handleErrorOverlayDismiss(msg)` — line 48: Handles dismissing the error overlay.\\n   - `a.handleDialogInput(msg, &amp;cmds)` — line 59: Forwards input events (key/mouse/paste) to the active dialog component.\\n   - `a.handleFilePickerInput(msg, &amp;cmds)` — line 62: Forwards input to the file picker.\\n   - `a.handleSettingsDialogInput(msg, &amp;cmds)` — line 65: Forwards input to the settings dialog.\\n\\n2. **Show-dialog cases in main switch (lines 69-380):** These are cases that trigger the *display* of dialogs when a `Show*` message arrives. There are 10 distinct `Show*Dialog` messages plus `ShowCommandsPalette` and `ShowQuitDialog`:\\n\\n   | Message | Handler | Dialog Purpose |\\n   |---------|---------|----------------|\\n   | `ShowCommandsPalette` | `openCommandsPalette()` | Command palette overlay |\\n   | `ShowQuitDialog` | `showQuitDialog()` | Quit confirmation |\\n   | `ShowAddProjectDialog` | `handleShowAddProjectDialog()` | Add project modal |\\n   | `ShowCreateWorkspaceDialog` | `handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog(msg)` | Create workspace modal |\\n   | `ShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog` | `handleShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog(msg)` | Delete workspace confirmation |\\n   | `ShowRemoveProjectDialog` | `handleShowRemoveProjectDialog(msg)` | Remove project confirmation |\\n   | `ShowSelectAssistantDialog` | `handleShowSelectAssistantDialog()` | Agent/assistant selector |\\n   | `ShowSelectTicketDialog` | `handleShowSelectTicketDialog()` | Ticket picker modal |\\n   | `ShowSettingsDialog` | `handleShowSettingsDialog()` | Settings modal |\\n   | `ShowCleanupTmuxDialog` | `handleShowCleanupTmuxDialog()` | Tmux session cleanup confirmation |\\n   | `ThemePreview` | `handleThemePreview(msg)` | Theme preview in settings |\\n   | `SettingsResult` | `handleSettingsResult(msg)` | Result from settings dialog actions |\\n\\n### Module Handling Summary\\n\\nThe file orchestrates several subsystems:\\n\\n| Module | Integration Points |\\n|--------|-------------------|\\n| **Toast notifications** | `common.ToastDismissed` (line 53), `messages.Toast` (line 265) with inner level switch |\\n| **Center pane (PTY tabs)** | PTY messages (line 252), tab creation/close/detach/reattach (lines 209-247), default fallthrough (line 373) |\\n| **Sidebar** | PTY messages (line 277), `OpenFileInEditor` (line 282) |\\n| **Dashboard** | `SpinnerTickMsg` (line 287), `TicketsLoadedMsg` forwarded (line 349) |\\n| **Git status** | `GitStatusResult` (line 139), `FileWatcherEvent` (line 320), `StateWatcherEvent` (line 323) |\\n| **Tmux integration** | 9 distinct message types (lines 298-318) |\\n| **Workspace lifecycle** | 12 distinct message types (creation, deletion, activation, scanning) |\\n| **Ticket system** | 5 message types (picker, selection, preview, store, loaded) |\\n| **Update/Upgrade** | `UpdateCheckComplete`, `TriggerUpgrade`, `UpgradeComplete` (lines 338-366) |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Follow-Up Suggestions\\n\\n1. **Dialog handler implementations** — The guard functions `handleDialogInput`, `handleFilePickerInput`, `handleSettingsDialogInput`, `handleDialogResultMsg`, and `handleErrorOverlayDismiss` are called here but defined elsewhere. Investigating those would clarify the full dialog input routing logic.\\n\\n2. **Message type definitions** — Many cases reference custom message types from `internal/messages` and `internal/ui/common`. Reading those packages would reveal the exact shape of dialog-related messages.\\n\\n3. **The `cmds` accumulation pattern** — The function uses a local `var cmds []tea.Cmd` slice and appends throughout, then returns `common.SafeBatch(cmds...)`. The `SafeBatch` helper (from `internal/ui/common`) would be worth examining to understand nil-cmd filtering.</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(5f55580e-bc73-4a05-a269-88af98982045) }, AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Analyze App struct fields to see how UICompositor is referenced - look at the App struct to find if it has a UICompositor field or embeds it.\\\"\\n>\\n<output>Here is the full analysis:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Summary\\n\\nInvestigated how `App` references `UICompositor` across the codebase. The answer is clear: **`UICompositor` is a plain pointer field, not an embedded type.**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Key Findings\\n\\n### 1. Declaration (pointer field, not embedded)\\n\\n`internal/app/app_core.go:71`:\\n```go\\nui *UICompositor\\n```\\n\\nThe field is declared as `ui *UICompositor` — a named pointer field. It is **not** embedded (which would be `UICompositor` without a name), so **no method promotion or field promotion occurs**. Every access to `UICompositor`'s members must go through `app.ui.*`.\\n\\nThe comment at `internal/app/app_core.go:70` explicitly describes the intent:\\n\\n&gt; `// UI Components (extracted to UICompositor)`\\n\\nindicating this was a deliberate extraction from a larger \\\"god object\\\" `App` into a separate struct.\\n\\n### 2. Initialization\\n\\n`internal/app/app_init.go:72`:\\n```go\\nui: newUICompositor(cfg, styles),\\n```\\n\\nThe constructor `newUICompositor` (`internal/app/ui_compositor.go:81-95`) initializes all non-lazy fields (layout, dashboard, center, sidebar, sidebarTerminal, toast, chrome caches).\\n\\n### 3. UICompositor struct itself\\n\\nDefined at `internal/app/ui_compositor.go:21-76`. It aggregates all core UI component models:\\n\\n| Field | Type | Notes |\\n|-------|------|-------|\\n| `layout` | `*layout.Manager` | Layout manager |\\n| `dashboard` | `*dashboard.Model` | Dashboard model |\\n| `center` | `*center.Model` | Center pane |\\n| `sidebar` | `*sidebar.TabbedSidebar` | Sidebar |\\n| `sidebarTerminal` | `*sidebar.TerminalModel` | Sidebar terminal |\\n| `dialog` | `*common.Dialog` | Lazy-created |\\n| `filePicker` | `*common.FilePicker` | Lazy-created |\\n| `settingsDialog` | `*common.SettingsDialog` | Lazy-created |\\n| `toast` | `*common.ToastModel` | Toast notifications |\\n\\nPlus dialog/picker context fields, layout dimensions, chrome caches, and settings state.\\n\\n### 4. Access pattern — always `app.ui.&lt;field&gt;` or `a.ui.&lt;field&gt;`\\n\\nSince `ui` is not embedded, all code uses explicit two-step access. Examples from real call sites:\\n\\n- `a.ui.dashboard` — `internal/app/app_input_workspace.go:24`\\n- `a.ui.center` — `internal/app/app_input_pty.go:12`\\n- `a.ui.sidebarTerminal` — `internal/app/app_input_workspace.go:102`\\n- `a.ui.layout.CenterWidth()` — `internal/app/app_view_content.go:15`\\n- `app.ui.centerBtnFocused` — `internal/app/app_workspace_activation_test.go:52`\\n- `app.ui.previewTicket` — `internal/app/app_view_content.go:34`\\n\\nThe pattern is uniform across **82+ occurrences** in 25+ files — always `receiver.ui.field`, never a promoted access.\\n\\n### 5. One method on UICompositor\\n\\n`UICompositor` has a single method: `canvasFor(width, height int) *lipgloss.Canvas` at `internal/app/ui_compositor.go:99-111`. Since the struct is not embedded, this is called as `a.ui.canvasFor(...)`, not `a.canvasFor(...)`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Insights and Context\\n\\n- **Extraction artifact**: `UICompositor` was carved out of `App` as part of \\\"gradual decomposition\\\" (`ui_compositor.go:18-19`). The `a.ui.` prefix is the visible cost of that extraction — a trade-off between a flatter namespace (embedding would promote) and explicitness about which struct owns what.\\n\\n- **No embedding chosen**: The team deliberately used a named field rather than embedding. This is a common Go pattern when the relationship is \\\"has-a\\\" (composition) rather than \\\"is-a\\\" (subtyping). It also prevents accidental shadowing if `App` later gains fields with the same names as `UICompositor` members.\\n\\n- **Test ergonomics**: Tests frequently construct `App{ui: &amp;UICompositor{...}}` directly (`internal/app/app_input_mouse_test.go:22` and many others), setting only the fields needed. This is possible precisely because `ui` is a named pointer field — tests can partially populate it without needing the full constructor.\\n\\n## Follow-up Suggestions\\n\\n- If you're considering refactoring further, the `app.ui.` indirection could be reduced by giving `App` methods that delegate to `ui` (e.g., `func (a *App) layoutManager() *layout.Manager { return a.ui.layout }`), though this adds boilerplate.\\n- The `harness.go` file (`internal/app/harness.go:138,196`) also uses `&amp;UICompositor{}` for headless rendering, which might be worth investigating for consistency with the main app path.</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(fd091e46-fa4d-44a0-87a0-c45883177f27) }, AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Find all handler methods related to dialogs by searching for func declarations containing 'Dialog' or 'dialog' in .go files under internal/.\\\"\\n>\\n<output>Here are all handler methods related to dialogs found under `internal/`, organized by file:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `internal/app/app_input_messages_dialogs.go` — Dialog Show Handlers\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 20 | `func (a *App) handleShowAddProjectDialog()` |\\n| 35 | `func (a *App) handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog(msg messages.ShowCreateWorkspaceDialog)` |\\n| 54 | `func (a *App) handleShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog(msg messages.ShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog)` |\\n| 68 | `func (a *App) handleShowRemoveProjectDialog(msg messages.ShowRemoveProjectDialog)` |\\n| 85 | `func (a *App) handleShowSelectAssistantDialog()` |\\n| 98 | `func (a *App) handleShowSelectTicketDialog() tea.Cmd` |\\n| 140 | `func (a *App) handleShowCleanupTmuxDialog()` |\\n| 155 | `func (a *App) handleShowSettingsDialog()` |\\n\\n### `internal/app/app_input_dialogs.go` — Dialog Input/Result Handlers\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 18 | `func (a *App) handleDialogResultMsg(msg tea.Msg) (bool, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 81 | `func (a *App) handleDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 93 | `func (a *App) handleSettingsDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 100 | `func (a *App) handleDialogResult(result common.DialogResult) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 244 | `func (a *App) showQuitDialog()` |\\n\\n### `internal/ui/common/dialog.go` — Dialog Builder Methods\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 134 | `func (d *Dialog) SetInputTransform(fn InputTransformFunc) *Dialog` |\\n| 140 | `func (d *Dialog) SetInputValidate(fn InputValidateFunc) *Dialog` |\\n\\n### `internal/ui/common/dialog_update.go` — Dialog Update\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 13 | `func (d *Dialog) Update(msg tea.Msg) (*Dialog, tea.Cmd)` |\\n\\n### `internal/ui/common/dialog_render.go` — Dialog Rendering\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 82 | `func (d *Dialog) dialogContentWidth() int` |\\n| 90 | `func (d *Dialog) dialogStyle() lipgloss.Style` |\\n| 98 | `func (d *Dialog) dialogFrame() (frameX, frameY, offsetX, offsetY int)` |\\n\\n### `internal/ui/common/filepicker_render.go` — FilePicker Dialog Methods\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 24 | `func (fp *FilePicker) dialogStyle() lipgloss.Style` |\\n| 32 | `func (fp *FilePicker) dialogFrame() (frameX, frameY, offsetX, offsetY int)` |\\n| 39 | `func (fp *FilePicker) dialogBounds(contentHeight int) (x, y, w, h int)` |\\n\\n### `internal/ui/common/settings.go` — SettingsDialog Methods\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 116 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) Update(msg tea.Msg) (*SettingsDialog, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 153 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) handleSelect() (*SettingsDialog, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 175 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) handleNextSection() (*SettingsDialog, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 188 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) handlePrevSection() (*SettingsDialog, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 202 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) handleNext() (*SettingsDialog, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 213 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) handlePrev() (*SettingsDialog, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 264 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) dialogContentWidth() int` |\\n| 271 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) dialogStyle() lipgloss.Style` |\\n\\n### `internal/ui/common/settings_render.go` — SettingsDialog Rendering\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 7 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) dialogFrame() (frameX, frameY, offsetX, offsetY int)` |\\n| 12 | `func (s *SettingsDialog) dialogBounds(contentHeight int) (x, y, w, h int)` |\\n\\n### `internal/ui/center/draft_filepicker.go` — Draft FilePicker Handler\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 42 | `func (d *Draft) handleFilePickerResult(msg common.DialogResult) (*Draft, tea.Cmd)` |\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Total: 33 dialog-related handler methods** across 8 files. The pattern reveals a clear separation: `app_input_messages_dialogs.go` handles *showing* dialogs, `app_input_dialogs.go` handles *input routing and results*, while `ui/common/` contains the core `Dialog` widget and its `SettingsDialog`/`FilePicker` specializations, each with their own `Update` loop and rendering logic.</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(ccfaeda9-eaed-4619-aa33-a4e903068dd0) }] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
