{"timestamp":"1434.830494589s","level":"DEBUG","fields":{"message":"Adding tool results to context","results":"[ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"read\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_00_8a6ktjXLoNRl9CGMc73C5CCm\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [Text(\"<file\\n  path=\\\"/tmp/forge_shell_stdout_h14KaH.txt\\\"\\n  display_lines=\\\"900-1063\\\"\\n  total_lines=\\\"1063\\\"\\n><![CDATA[ 900:\\n 901:If lint_command is set:\\n 902:```bash\\n 903:{{lint_command}}\\n 904:```\\n 905:\\n 906:**Exit criteria:** Code compiles. Obvious regressions caught. Ready to submit.\\n 907:\\n 908:### Step 7: Pre-merge rebase verification\\n 909:\\n 910:Rebase onto the target branch and run the full gate suite. This enables the\\n 911:refinery to fast-path merge your MR without re-running gates (~5s merge\\n 912:instead of minutes).\\n 913:\\n 914:**1. Fetch and rebase onto target:**\\n 915:```bash\\n 916:git fetch origin main\\n 917:git rebase origin/main\\n 918:```\\n 919:\\n 920:If rebase conflicts:\\n 921:- Resolve them carefully\\n 922:- Re-run the build to ensure the resolution is correct\\n 923:- If stuck, mail Witness\\n 924:\\n 925:**2. Run the full gate suite on the rebased result:**\\n 926:\\n 927:Run ALL configured gates (not just targeted tests — this is the full verification):\\n 928:\\n 929:If build_command is set:\\n 930:```bash\\n 931:{{build_command}}\\n 932:```\\n 933:\\n 934:If typecheck_command is set:\\n 935:```bash\\n 936:{{typecheck_command}}\\n 937:```\\n 938:\\n 939:If lint_command is set:\\n 940:```bash\\n 941:{{lint_command}}\\n 942:```\\n 943:\\n 944:If test_command is set:\\n 945:```bash\\n 946:{{test_command}}\\n 947:```\\n 948:\\n 949:Empty commands mean \\\"not configured\\\" — skip silently.\\n 950:\\n 951:**3. If any gate fails after rebase:**\\n 952:- Fix the issue, commit, and re-run from step 1\\n 953:- Do NOT proceed with --pre-verified if gates failed\\n 954:\\n 955:**4. If all gates pass:**\\n 956:You will use `gt done --pre-verified` in the next step. This tells the refinery\\n 957:that you ran the full gate suite on a rebased branch, enabling fast-path merge.\\n 958:\\n 959:**Note:** If this step takes too long or the gates are not configured for this\\n 960:project, you may skip this step and use `gt done` without --pre-verified.\\n 961:The refinery will run gates normally (slower but still correct).\\n 962:\\n 963:**Exit criteria:** Branch rebased onto latest origin/main, all configured gates pass.\\n 964:\\n 965:### Step 8: Submit work and self-clean\\n 966:\\n 967:Submit your work and clean up. You cease to exist after this step.\\n 968:\\n 969:**Self-Cleaning Model:**\\n 970:Once you run `gt done`, you're gone. The command:\\n 971:1. Pushes your branch to origin\\n 972:2. Creates an MR bead in the merge queue\\n 973:3. Nukes your sandbox (worktree removal)\\n 974:4. Exits your session immediately\\n 975:\\n 976:**Pre-flight: Verify you have actual work to submit (HARD GATE):**\\n 977:```bash\\n 978:git log origin/main..HEAD --oneline\\n 979:```\\n 980:This MUST show at least 1 commit. If it shows nothing, do NOT run `gt done`.\\n 981:`gt done` will reject zero-commit branches for polecats.\\n 982:\\n 983:**Run gt done:**\\n 984:```bash\\n 985:# For code tasks with pre-verification (recommended — enables fast-path merge):\\n 986:gt done --pre-verified --target main\\n 987:\\n 988:# For code tasks without pre-verification (gates skipped or failed):\\n 989:gt done --target main\\n 990:\\n 991:# For report-only tasks (no commits — audits, reviews, research):\\n 992:gt done --status DEFERRED\\n 993:```\\n 994:\\n 995:You should see output like:\\n 996:```\\n 997:✓ Work submitted to merge queue\\n 998:  MR ID: gt-xxxxx\\n 999:  Source: polecat/<name>\\n1000:  Target: main\\n1001:  Issue: {{issue}}\\n1002:✓ Sandbox nuked\\n1003:✓ Session exiting\\n1004:```\\n1005:\\n1006:**What happens next (not your concern):**\\n1007:- Refinery batches MRs and runs gates on the merged stack\\n1008:- If green: all MRs in the batch merge to main at once\\n1009:- If red: Refinery bisects to isolate the culprit, merges the good ones\\n1010:- Refinery fixes failures itself (inline or via helper polecats)\\n1011:- Refinery closes your issue after successful merge\\n1012:\\n1013:You are NOT involved in any of that. You're gone. Done means gone.\\n1014:\\n1015:**Exit criteria:** Work submitted, sandbox nuked, session exited.\\n1016:\\n1017:\\n1018:Work through ALL steps above, including submit and cleanup.\\n1019:The base bead is your assignment. The formula steps define your workflow.\\n1020:\\n1021:REQUIRED: When all steps complete, run `gt done` to submit to the merge queue. Do NOT stop after implementation — the formula has submit steps you must follow.\\n1022:\\n1023:# Gas Town Worker Context\\n1024:\\n1025:> **Context Recovery**: Run `gt prime` for full context after compaction or new session.\\n1026:\\n1027:## The Propulsion Principle (GUPP)\\n1028:\\n1029:**If you find work on your hook, YOU RUN IT.**\\n1030:\\n1031:No confirmation. No waiting. No announcements. The hook having work IS the assignment.\\n1032:This is physics, not politeness. Gas Town is a steam engine - you are a piston.\\n1033:\\n1034:**Failure mode we're preventing:**\\n1035:- Agent starts with work on hook\\n1036:- Agent announces itself and waits for human to say \\\"ok go\\\"\\n1037:- Human is AFK / trusting the engine to run\\n1038:- Work sits idle. The whole system stalls.\\n1039:\\n1040:## Startup Protocol\\n1041:\\n1042:1. Check your hook: `gt mol status`\\n1043:2. If work is hooked → EXECUTE (no announcement, no waiting)\\n1044:3. If hook empty → Check mail: `gt mail inbox`\\n1045:4. Still nothing? Wait for user instructions\\n1046:\\n1047:## Key Commands\\n1048:\\n1049:- `gt prime` - Get full role context (run after compaction)\\n1050:- `gt mol status` - Check your hooked work\\n1051:- `gt mail inbox` - Check for messages\\n1052:- `bd ready` - Find available work (no blockers)\\n1053:\\n1054:## Session Close Protocol\\n1055:\\n1056:Before signaling completion:\\n1057:1. git status (check what changed)\\n1058:2. git add <files> (stage code changes)\\n1059:3. git commit -m \\\"...\\\" (commit code)\\n1060:4. git push (push to remote)\\n1061:5. `gt done` (submit to merge queue and exit)\\n1062:\\n1063:**Polecats MUST call `gt done` - this submits work and exits the session.**]]>\\n</file>\")] } }, ToolResult { name: ToolName(\"task\"), call_id: Some(ToolCallId(\"call_01_CP7aIlX8szsKDqsxDDsadcud\")), output: ToolOutput { is_error: false, values: [AI { value: \"<task_completed\\n  task=\\\"Explore the codebase structure to understand: 1) Where is App defined and what does it look like? 2) Where is UICompositor defined? 3) Where are the handler methods (app_input_messages_dialogs.go, app_input_dialogs.go)? 4) Where is app_input.go and what switch cases need updating? 5) What fields does UICompositor already have? 6) What is the current relationship between App and UICompositor? Report all file paths, relevant line numbers, and the current structure.\\\"\\n>\\n<output># Codebase Structure Report\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. App Struct Definition\\n\\n**File:** `internal/app/app_core.go:40-126`\\n\\n`App` is the root Bubble Tea model, containing ~43 fields across 11 logical groups:\\n\\n| Group | Lines | Fields |\\n|-------|-------|--------|\\n| **Configuration** | 42-51 | `config`, `workspaceService`, `gitStatus`, `tmuxService`, `updateService`, `modelRegistry`, `ticketServices`, `doltStores`, `ticketRenderer`, `discoveryReady` |\\n| **Limits** | 54 | `maxAttachedAgentTabs` |\\n| **State** | 57-61 | `projects`, `activeWorkspace`, `activeProject`, `focusedPane`, `showWelcome` |\\n| **Update state** | 64-68 | `updateAvailable`, `version`, `commit`, `buildDate`, `upgradeRunning` |\\n| **UI Components** | 71 | `ui *UICompositor` |\\n| **Git status** | 74 | `gitStatusController` |\\n| **Layout/Lifecycle/Prefix** | 77-88 | `keymap`, `err`, `shutdownOnce`, `ctx`, `supervisor`, `prefixActive`, `prefixToken`, `prefixSequence`, `prefixLabel`, `prefixHelpLabel` |\\n| **Tmux state** | 90-106 | 18 fields (sync, activity scanning, options, availability, session states, `instanceID`) |\\n| **Workspace lifecycle** | 109 | `workspaceManager` |\\n| **Terminal/Perf** | 112-116 | `keyboardEnhancements`, `lastInputAt`, `pendingInputLatency` |\\n| **External pump &amp; poller** | 119-125 | `externalMsgs`, `externalCritical`, `externalSender`, `externalOnce`, `ticketPoller` |\\n\\nDialog ID constants are at `internal/app/app_core.go:23-32`:\\n```\\nDialogAddProject, DialogCreateWorkspace, DialogDeleteWorkspace, DialogRemoveProject,\\nDialogSelectAssistant, DialogSelectTicket, DialogQuit, DialogCleanupTmux\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. UICompositor Struct Definition\\n\\n**File:** `internal/app/ui_compositor.go:21-76`\\n\\n```go\\ntype UICompositor struct {\\n    // Core UI components (lines 22-30)\\n    layout          *layout.Manager\\n    dashboard       *dashboard.Model\\n    center          *center.Model\\n    sidebar         *sidebar.TabbedSidebar\\n    sidebarTerminal *sidebar.TerminalModel\\n    dialog          *common.Dialog         // lazy-created\\n    filePicker      *common.FilePicker     // lazy-created\\n    settingsDialog  *common.SettingsDialog // lazy-created\\n    toast           *common.ToastModel\\n\\n    // Dialog/picker context (lines 33-40)\\n    dialogProject           *data.Project\\n    dialogWorkspace         *data.Workspace\\n    pendingWorkspaceProject *data.Project\\n    pendingWorkspaceName    string\\n    pendingWorkspaceBase    string\\n    pendingTickets          []tickets.Ticket\\n    previewTicket           *tickets.Ticket\\n    previewProject          *data.Project\\n\\n    // Layout dimensions and visual state (lines 43-47)\\n    width, height int\\n    canvas        *lipgloss.Canvas\\n    styles        common.Styles\\n    ready         bool\\n    quitting      bool\\n\\n    // Chrome caches for layer-based rendering (lines 50-66)\\n    dashboardChrome      *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    centerChrome         *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    sidebarChrome        *compositor.ChromeCache\\n    // + 14 inline cache fields (drawableCache / borderCache)\\n\\n    // Button focus state (lines 69-70)\\n    centerBtnFocused bool\\n    centerBtnIndex   int\\n\\n    // Settings theme dialog state (lines 73-75)\\n    settingsDialogSession       int\\n    settingsThemePersistedTheme common.ThemeID\\n    settingsThemeDirty          bool\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Constructor:** `newUICompositor()` at `ui_compositor.go:81-95` — initializes non-lazy fields only. Lazy fields (`dialog`, `filePicker`, `settingsDialog`, `canvas`) start as `nil`.\\n\\n**Direct methods:** Only `canvasFor(width, height int) *lipgloss.Canvas` at `ui_compositor.go:99-111`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Dialog Handler Files\\n\\n### 3a. `internal/app/app_input_messages_dialogs.go` (340 lines)\\nHandles *showing* dialogs in response to messages:\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 20 | `func (a *App) handleShowAddProjectDialog()` |\\n| 35 | `func (a *App) handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog(msg messages.ShowCreateWorkspaceDialog)` |\\n| 54 | `func (a *App) handleShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog(msg messages.ShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog)` |\\n| 68 | `func (a *App) handleShowRemoveProjectDialog(msg messages.ShowRemoveProjectDialog)` |\\n| 85 | `func (a *App) handleShowSelectAssistantDialog()` |\\n| 98 | `func (a *App) handleShowSelectTicketDialog() tea.Cmd` |\\n| 117 | `func (a *App) handleTicketsForPickerLoaded(msg ticketsForPickerLoaded)` |\\n| 140 | `func (a *App) handleShowCleanupTmuxDialog()` |\\n| 155 | `func (a *App) handleShowSettingsDialog()` |\\n| 183 | `func (a *App) applyTheme(theme common.ThemeID)` |\\n| 200 | `func (a *App) handleThemePreview(msg common.ThemePreview) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 211 | `func (a *App) persistSettingsThemeIfDirty() tea.Cmd` |\\n| 225 | `func (a *App) handleSettingsResult(_ common.SettingsResult) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 236 | `func (a *App) handleTicketSelected(msg messages.TicketSelectedMsg) []tea.Cmd` |\\n| 275 | `func (a *App) handleTicketPreview(msg messages.TicketPreviewMsg)` |\\n\\n### 3b. `internal/app/app_input_dialogs.go` (346 lines)\\nHandles dialog *input routing* and *result dispatching*:\\n\\n| Line | Signature |\\n|------|-----------|\\n| 18 | `func (a *App) handleDialogResultMsg(msg tea.Msg) (bool, tea.Cmd)` |\\n| 34 | `func (a *App) handleErrorOverlayDismiss(msg tea.Msg) bool` |\\n| 48 | `func handleOverlayInput[T ...](overlay T, msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd, consumePaste bool) (T, bool)` — **generic** |\\n| 81 | `func (a *App) handleDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 87 | `func (a *App) handleFilePickerInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 93 | `func (a *App) handleSettingsDialogInput(msg tea.Msg, cmds *[]tea.Cmd) bool` |\\n| 100 | `func (a *App) handleDialogResult(result common.DialogResult) tea.Cmd` — **central dispatcher** |\\n| 244 | `func (a *App) showQuitDialog()` |\\n| 259 | `func (a *App) handleUpdateCheckComplete(msg messages.UpdateCheckComplete) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 284 | `func (a *App) handleTriggerUpgrade() tea.Cmd` |\\n| 318 | `func (a *App) handleUpgradeComplete(msg messages.UpgradeComplete) tea.Cmd` |\\n| 335 | `func (a *App) handleOpenFileInEditor(msg sidebar.OpenFileInEditor) tea.Cmd` |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. app_input.go — Analysis\\n\\n**File:** `internal/app/app_input.go` (390 lines)\\n\\n### Structure\\nThe `update()` method at `app_input.go:31-383` uses a **two-tier dispatch**:\\n\\n**Tier 1 — Pre-switch overlay guards (lines 39-67):**\\nThese intercept messages *before* the main type switch:\\n1. **Perf tracking** (lines 39-43): Marks `KeyPressMsg`, `KeyReleaseMsg`, `MouseClickMsg`, `MouseWheelMsg`, `MouseMotionMsg`, `MouseReleaseMsg`, `PasteMsg`\\n2. **Dialog result routing** (line 45-47): `handleDialogResultMsg(msg)` — consumes `DialogResult` from any active dialog\\n3. **Error overlay dismiss** (line 48-50): `handleErrorOverlayDismiss(msg)`\\n4. **Toast dismiss** (line 53-57): `common.ToastDismissed`\\n5. **Overlay input gates** (lines 59-67): `handleDialogInput`, `handleFilePickerInput`, `handleSettingsDialogInput` — consume `KeyPressMsg`/`MouseClickMsg`/`PasteMsg` *before* they reach pane routing\\n\\n**Tier 2 — Main type switch (lines 69-380):**\\nKey case categories related to dialogs/modules:\\n\\n| Lines | Case | Handler |\\n|-------|------|---------|\\n| 103-106 | `messages.ShowCommandsPalette` | `a.openCommandsPalette()` |\\n| 114-115 | `messages.ShowQuitDialog` | `a.showQuitDialog()` |\\n| 142-143 | `messages.ShowAddProjectDialog` | `a.handleShowAddProjectDialog()` |\\n| 145-146 | `messages.ShowCreateWorkspaceDialog` | `a.handleShowCreateWorkspaceDialog(msg)` |\\n| 148-149 | `messages.ShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog` | `a.handleShowDeleteWorkspaceDialog(msg)` |\\n| 151-152 | `messages.ShowRemoveProjectDialog` | `a.handleShowRemoveProjectDialog(msg)` |\\n| 154-155 | `messages.ShowSelectAssistantDialog` | `a.handleShowSelectAssistantDialog()` |\\n| 157-160 | `messages.ShowSelectTicketDialog` | `a.handleShowSelectTicketDialog()` |\\n| 162-163 | `ticketsForPickerLoaded` | `a.handleTicketsForPickerLoaded(msg)` |\\n| 165-166 | `messages.TicketSelectedMsg` | `a.handleTicketSelected(msg)` |\\n| 168-169 | `messages.TicketPreviewMsg` | `a.handleTicketPreview(msg)` |\\n| 171-172 | `messages.ShowSettingsDialog` | `a.handleShowSettingsDialog()` |\\n| 174-175 | `messages.ShowCleanupTmuxDialog` | `a.handleShowCleanupTmuxDialog()` |\\n| 177-180 | `common.ThemePreview` | `a.handleThemePreview(msg)` |\\n| 182-185 | `common.SettingsResult` | `a.handleSettingsResult(msg)` |\\n| 373-379 | `default` | Forwards to `a.ui.center.Update(msg)` |\\n\\n### Areas needing updates for dialog/module handling:\\n1. **Overlay input gate** (lines 59-67): Adding a new overlay type requires adding a new guard here\\n2. **Dialog ID list** in `handleDialogResultMsg` at `app_input_dialogs.go:25`: hard-coded string switch that must stay in sync with constants at `app_core.go:23-32`\\n3. **Overlay visibility** functions (`overlayVisible()`, `overlayCursor()`, `composeOverlays()` in `app_view_overlays.go`) all need updating for new overlay types\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. UICompositor Fields Summary\\n\\n| Category | Fields |\\n|----------|--------|\\n| **Core UI models** | `layout`, `dashboard`, `center`, `sidebar`, `sidebarTerminal`, `dialog`*, `filePicker`*, `settingsDialog`*, `toast` |\\n| **Dialog/picker context** | `dialogProject`, `dialogWorkspace`, `pendingWorkspaceProject`, `pendingWorkspaceName`, `pendingWorkspaceBase`, `pendingTickets`, `previewTicket`, `previewProject` |\\n| **Layout &amp; visual** | `width`, `height`, `canvas`*, `styles`, `ready`, `quitting` |\\n| **Chrome caches** | `dashboardChrome`, `centerChrome`, `sidebarChrome` + 14 inline caches |\\n| **Button state** | `centerBtnFocused`, `centerBtnIndex` |\\n| **Settings state** | `settingsDialogSession`, `settingsThemePersistedTheme`, `settingsThemeDirty` |\\n\\n(* = lazy-created)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. App ↔ UICompositor Relationship\\n\\n- **Ownership:** `App` holds `UICompositor` as a named pointer field (`ui *UICompositor` at `app_core.go:71`) — it is **not embedded**, so no field/method promotion occurs\\n- **Initialization:** `app_init.go:72` sets `ui: newUICompositor(cfg, styles)`\\n- **Access pattern:** Always `a.ui.&lt;field&gt;` (82+ occurrences across 25+ files), never promoted access\\n- **Architectural role:** `UICompositor` is a subordinate data holder containing all visual model state; `App` retains business logic, services, lifecycle, and message routing\\n\\n### Access examples:\\n| Pattern | Example |\\n|---------|---------|\\n| Pane models | `a.ui.center`, `a.ui.dashboard`, `a.ui.sidebar`, `a.ui.sidebarTerminal` |\\n| Overlays | `a.ui.dialog`, `a.ui.filePicker`, `a.ui.settingsDialog` |\\n| Dialog context | `a.ui.dialogProject`, `a.ui.pendingTickets` |\\n| Rendering | `a.ui.canvas`, `a.ui.styles` |\\n| Chrome caches | `a.ui.dashboardChrome`, `a.ui.centerChrome` |</output>\\n</task_completed>\", conversation_id: ConversationId(1656d6d0-163b-4ad4-b073-566fe4d79d5e) }] } }]"},"filename":"crates/forge_domain/src/context.rs","line_number":515}
